\h Luke
\toc1 Luke
\toc2 Luke
\toc3 Luke
\mt2 The first account by
\mt1 Luke
\mt2 being the account of Yeshua's ministry
\is1 Introduction
\is2 Author
\ip This account about the works and teachings of Yeshua was written by Luke, one of the later followers of Yeshua. Luke was believed to be a medical doctor and although many have assumed him to be a Greek, there's also a good case that he was Jewish. He was good friends with Paul and accompanied him several times as they travelled to various places to spread the good message about Yeshua the messiah. Luke was also the author of the account of the beginnings of the Christian church known commonly known as \bk Acts\bk*, and unlike most other Bibles, the \em Open English Translation\em* places these two successive accounts one after the other.
\is2 This account
\ip This account was written to Theophilus who is said to be an honoured person from Rome. He starts his account with the prophesied birth of Yohan-the-immerser and then of Yeshua right through until he's lifted into the clouds. Luke also explains how that Yeshua is the messiah promised by God to save Jews and all non-Jews who put their trust in him.
\ip It's also told here in this document about Yeshua's mercy towards troubled people and sinners, his healing of many who were sick or possessed by demons, his bringing dead people back to life, and his teaching. Recurring themes here include God's spirit, prayer, forgiveness of sins, the women who helped Yeshua with his work, and how believers should prepare for his return.
\iot Main components of Luke's first account
\io1 Introduction \ior 1:1-4\ior*
\io1 The birth and childhood of Yohan-the-immerser and of Yeshua \ior 1:5вҖ“2:52\ior*
\io1 The ministry of Yohan-the-immerser \ior 3:1-20\ior*
\io1 The immersion and testing of Yeshua \ior 3:21вҖ“4:13\ior*
\io1 Yeshua's ministry up in Galilee \ior 4:14вҖ“9:50\ior*
\io1 Moving from Galilee towards Yerushalem \ior 9:51вҖ“19:27\ior*
\io1 The final week in and near Yerushalem \ior 19:28вҖ“23:56\ior*
\io1 The resurrection, appearances, and exit of Yeshua \ior 24:1-53\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Introduction
\rem /s1 Dedication to Theophilus
\p
\v 1 Several people attemptedВҰ37265 to write an account about the events that we're personally certain of
\v 2 as the ones who were eyewitnessesВҰ37283 andВҰ37284 hearers of these accounts from the beginningВҰ37282 handed them over to us.
\v 3 So since we had followedВҰ37292 all these events so carefully, itВҰ37290 seemed like a good idea to writeВҰ37298 this account for youВҰ37297, honoured TheophilusВҰ37300,
\v 4 so thatВҰ37305 you could knowВҰ37302 the definite background behind what you were taught.
\s1 The messenger foretells the birth of Yohan-the-immerser
\rem /s1 The Birth of John the Baptist Is Announced; The Birth of John the Baptist Foretold; The coming of Christ
\p
\v 5 \x + \xo 1:5: \xt 1Ch 24:10.\x*It started with the priestВҰ37319 Zekaryah \add (Zechariah)\add* and his wifeВҰ37328 Elizabeth at the time when HerodВҰ37314 was the kingВҰ37316 of YudeaВҰ37318. (Zekaryah was in the priestly divisionВҰ37324 of Abiyah, and Elizabeth was also a descendant of AaronВҰ37334.)
\v 6 \nd GodВҰ37348\nd* considered them both good and blamelessВҰ37358 as theyВҰ37341 followed his instructions and obeyed his rules.
\v 7 ElizabethВҰ37367 had never been able to have a childВҰ37363, so there was just the two of them as they were now getting older.
\p
\v 8 One timeВҰ37382 as he was taking his rostered turn to serve \nd GodВҰ37394\nd* along with his divisionВҰ37389,
\v 9 he was chosenВҰ37400 by lot (this was how the priestsВҰ37399 assigned tasks) to light the incenseВҰ37403 in the templeВҰ37407, and so he proceeded inside.
\v 10 A lot of peopleВҰ37417 would be prayingВҰ37419 outsideВҰ37420 the temple at the time when the incenseВҰ37424 was burnt.
\v 11 At that moment, a messengerВҰ37428 from God appearedВҰ37425 to Zekaryah, standing right there at the right of the incenseВҰ37436 altarВҰ37434.
\v 12 ZekaryahВҰ37439 got a big fright at seeing him there andВҰ37437 started to tremble.
\v 13 But the messengerВҰ37452 spoke, вҖңDon't be scared Zekaryah, becauseВҰ37457 your request has been listenedВҰ37458 to, and your wifeВҰ37464 ElizabethВҰ37466 will give birth to a son and you'll nameВҰ37475 him Yohan.
\v 14 He'll bring a lot of happiness to you andВҰ37478 you'll be proud of himВҰ37491вҖ”in fact many people will be glad.
\v 15 \x + \xo 1:15: \xt Num 6:3.\x*He'll be considered special in God's eyes, but he won'tВҰ37506 be allowed to drinkВҰ37507 wine or spirits. Even while he's stillВҰ37512 in hisВҰ37518 mother'sВҰ37517 womb, he'll be filledВҰ37511 with God's \nd spiritВҰ37509\nd*.
\v 16 He will turn many children of Yisrael back to \nd YahwehВҰ37526\nd*, theirВҰ37529 \nd GodВҰ37528\nd*.
\v 17 \x + \xo 1:17: \xt Mal 4:5-6.\x*And he will go on aheadВҰ37533 of God with the spiritВҰ37537 and the powerВҰ37539 of Eliyah, to turn fathersВҰ37544 back to loving their childrenВҰ37546 and to turn career criminals towards the wisdom of godlyВҰ37551 people, to get the people ready for \nd YahwehВҰ37554\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 Zekaryah asked the messengerВҰ37562, вҖңHow will I know if \add вүҲyou're telling the truth\add*, becauseВҰ37568 I'm an olderВҰ37570 manВҰ37570 andВҰ37571 myВҰ37574 wifeВҰ37573 is also getting old?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \x + \xo 1:19: \xt Dan 8:16; 9:21.\x*Now the messengerВҰ37583 rebuked himВҰ37585, вҖңI am GabrielВҰ37588 who stoodВҰ37590 right in front of \nd GodВҰ37593\nd* and was commanded to come here and talk to you, and to tell all of this to you,
\v 20 so listen to this: Because you didn'tВҰ37608 believeВҰ37620 myВҰ37623 messageВҰ37622, you'll be made silentВҰ37606 and unable to speakВҰ37610 untilВҰ37611 the dayВҰ37613 thatВҰ37624 all of theseВҰ37616 things happen, and they certainly will happen at the proper times.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 Meanwhile, the peopleВҰ37634 outside were expectingВҰ37636 Zekaryah to come back out, andВҰ37639 were wondering what could be holding himВҰ37645 up there inside the templeВҰ37648.
\v 22 ButВҰ37664 when he did emerge, he wasn't able to speakВҰ37654 to them. They wondering if maybe he'd seenВҰ37660 a visionВҰ37659 in the templeВҰ37663, andВҰ37664 he nodded to confirm this although he remained mute,
\v 23 andВҰ37673 after he'd finished hisВҰ37681 rostered daysВҰ37678 in the temple, he returned homeВҰ37686.
\p
\v 24 As time went on, ElizabethВҰ37697 became pregnant andВҰ37701 secludedВҰ37702 herselfВҰ37703 away for fiveВҰ37705 monthsВҰ37704, sayingВҰ37706,
\v 25 вҖң\nd YahwehВҰ37712\nd* has done this for me. At this time he's lookedВҰ37716 down at me and taken away the public shame of myВҰ37720 being childless.вҖқ
\s1 God's messenger comes to Maria
\rem /s1 The Birth of Jesus Foretold; The Birth of Jesus Is Announced
\p
\v 26 When Elizabeth was six monthsВҰ37726 pregnant, \nd GodВҰ37737\nd* sentВҰ37730 his messengerВҰ37732 GabrielВҰ37733 to \nd NazarethВҰ37746\nd*, a cityВҰ37739 in the GalileeВҰ37742 region.
\v 27 \x + \xo 1:27: \xt Mat 1:18.\x*Gabriel went to a young woman named MariaВҰ37765 who was engaged to be married to Yosef, a descendant of \add King\add* DavidВҰ37759,
\v 28 and entering the room, spoke to herВҰ37772, вҖңHello there. \nd YahwehВҰ37779\nd* is with you and he's chosen you to be honoured.вҖқ
\v 29 Maria was very puzzled by the statementВҰ37793 andВҰ37797 wondered what kind of greetingВҰ37805 it could be
\v 30 as the messengerВҰ37811 continuedВҰ37808, вҖңDon't be scared, MariaВҰ37817, becauseВҰ37820 \nd GodВҰ37824\nd* is showing his favourВҰ37821 on youВҰ37819,
\v 31 \x + \xo 1:31: \xt Mat 1:21.\x*and listen, you'll conceiveВҰ37827 a baby and go on to give birth to a son, and you must nameВҰ37836 himВҰ37837 \nd YeshuaВҰ37838\nd*.
\v 32 \x + \xo 1:32-33: \xt 2Sam 7:12-13,16; Isa 9:7.\x*He'll be very special and will be calledВҰ37846 вҖҳthe son of the highestВҰ37845 oneвҖҷ, and \nd YahwehВҰ37851 GodВҰ37853\nd* will give him the throneВҰ37855 of DavidВҰ37856, hisВҰ37859 ancestor.
\v 33 He'll reignВҰ37861 over Yacob's descendants throughout the ages, and hisВҰ37872 kingdomВҰ37871 will never endВҰ37875.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖңHow would this work,вҖқ MariaВҰ37879 asked the messengerВҰ37882, вҖңbecauseВҰ37887 I've never slept with a guy?вҖқ
\p
\v 35 вҖңThe holy \nd spiritВҰ37898\nd* will come over you,вҖқ answeredВҰ37893 the messengerВҰ37895, вҖңand the powerВҰ37904 of the highestВҰ37905 one will overshadowВҰ37906 you, and so the holy childВҰ37915 that'll be born will be calledВҰ37916 God's son.
\v 36 Also, yourВҰ37925 relativeВҰ37923 ElizabethВҰ37921 has also conceivedВҰ37929 a son in herВҰ37933 old ageвҖ”the one who was calledВҰ37942 barrenВҰ37943 is now six monthsВҰ37937 pregnant
\v 37 \x + \xo 1:37: \xt Gen 18:14.\x*because with \nd GodВҰ37955\nd*, his statements always come to pass.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 вҖңListenВҰ37963,вҖқ said MariaВҰ37962, вҖңI'm \nd Yahweh's\nd* servant girl. May everything you said come true.вҖқ ThenВҰ37961 the messengerВҰ37979 left her.
\s1 Maria's visit to Elizabeth
\rem /s1 Mary Visits Elizabeth
\p
\v 39 Several daysВҰ37986 later, MariaВҰ37983 determined that she'd go to the town in the hills of Yudea
\v 40 where Zekaryah and Elizabeth lived. She entered the houseВҰ38002 and greetedВҰ38005 Elizabeth,
\v 41 and as soon as ElizabethВҰ38019 heardВҰ38011 the greetingВҰ38015, her baby in her womb kickedВҰ38020, and she was filledВҰ38034 with the holy \nd spiritВҰ38035\nd*
\v 42 and sheВҰ38041 called out loudlyВҰ38044, вҖңOut of \add all\add* womenВҰ38050, youВҰ38057 have been blessed and the baby in yourВҰ38057 womb has been blessed.
\v 43 How could this happen to meвҖ”that the motherВҰ38065 of myВҰ38068 \nd masterВҰ38067\nd* would comeВҰ38063 andВҰ38058 visit me!
\v 44 You seeВҰ38071, as soon as I heard yourВҰ38079 greetingВҰ38078, the baby in myВҰ38083 womb kickedВҰ38084 with excitement,
\v 45 andВҰ38095 the womanВҰ38099 who believedВҰ38100 that everything \nd YahwehВҰ38108\nd* told herВҰ38106 will happen, she will be blessedВҰ38098.вҖқ
\s1 Maria's song of praise
\rem /s1 The Magnificat: Mary's Song of Praise
\p
\v 46 MariaВҰ38111 saidВҰ38110,
\q1 вҖңMyВҰ38115 soulВҰ38114 praises \nd YahwehВҰ38117\nd*,
\q1
\v 47 andВҰ38118 my spiritВҰ38121 is so happy about \nd GodВҰ38126\nd*, my saviourВҰ38128,
\q1
\v 48 \x + \xo 1:48: \xt 1Sam 1:11.\x*becauseВҰ38140 he noticed hisВҰ38138 humble servant girl.
\q1 Look now, all the future generationsВҰ38148 will consider that I was blessedВҰ38144
\q1
\v 49 because the powerfulВҰ38157 one treated me incredibly,
\q1 andВҰ38158 hisВҰ38163 nameВҰ38162 is holy.
\q1
\v 50 He shows hisВҰ38167 mercyВҰ38166 to multiple generations;
\q1 to those who honour him.
\q1
\v 51 HisВҰ38182 arm is powerfulВҰ38179;
\q1 he scattersВҰ38183 those who are proudВҰ38184 in theirВҰ38187 heartsВҰ38186.
\q1
\v 52 \x + \xo 1:52: \xt Yob 5:11; 12:19.\x*He knocks kings off their thronesВҰ38191,
\q1 andВҰ38192 praises those who are humbleВҰ38194.
\q1
\v 53 Those who are hungry, he fills with goodВҰ38197 things,
\q1 but those who are rich, he sends away emptyВҰ38201 handed.
\q1
\v 54 He tookВҰ38202 good care of hisВҰ38205 servantВҰ38204, Yisrael,
\q1 to be remindedВҰ38206 of mercyВҰ38207
\q1
\v 55 \x + \xo 1:55: \xt Gen 17:7.\x*as he spokeВҰ38209 to ourВҰ38213 ancestorsВҰ38212,
\q1 to AbrahamВҰ38215 and hisВҰ38219 descendantsВҰ38218,
\q1 at the right time.вҖқ
\p
\v 56 SoВҰ38226 MariaВҰ38227 stayed with Elizabeth for aboutВҰ38230 threeВҰ38233 monthsВҰ38232 before returningВҰ38235 back to herВҰ38239 own homeВҰ38238.
\s1 The birth of Yohan-the-immerser
\rem /s1 The Birth of John the Baptist
\p
\v 57 When Elizabeth's nine months were up, sheВҰ38250 gave birth andВҰ38249 produced a son
\v 58 and her neighboursВҰ38255 and relativesВҰ38258 heardВҰ38253 that \nd YahwehВҰ38263\nd* had shown great mercyВҰ38265 to her, and so they celebrated along with her.
\p
\v 59 \x + \xo 1:59: \xt Lev 12:3.\x*When the baby boy was eightВҰ38279 days old, it was the time to circumciseВҰ38281 him, andВҰ38272 \add the relatives at the ceremony\add* started callingВҰ38285 him ZachariasВҰ38293 afterВҰ38287 the nameВҰ38289 of hisВҰ38292 fatherВҰ38291,
\v 60 butВҰ38301 the baby's motherВҰ38297 spoke up andВҰ38294 saidВҰ38299, вҖңNo, he's going to be named Yohan.вҖқ
\p
\v 61 вҖңNone of yourВҰ38320 relativesВҰ38318 have that nameВҰ38325,вҖқ theyВҰ38308 saidВҰ38308
\v 62 andВҰ38330 they signalledВҰ38329 to the fatherВҰ38332 to tell them what nameВҰ38334 he wanted for the baby.
\p
\v 63 SoВҰ38343 Zacharias requestedВҰ38344 a writing tabletВҰ38346 andВҰ38343 wroteВҰ38347, вҖңHisВҰ38354 nameВҰ38353 is Yohan.вҖқ Everyone was amazed
\v 64 and thenВҰ38365 suddenly hisВҰ38369 mouthВҰ38368 and tongueВҰ38373 were freed and he was able to speakВҰ38376 again and started praising \nd GodВҰ38379\nd*.
\v 65 EveryoneВҰ38398 who lived nearby was a bit unnerved by all this, andВҰ38392 the story about what happened was discussedВҰ38401 \add in all the homes\add* aroundВҰ38389 the hills
\v 66 andВҰ38407 those who heardВҰ38411 about it were thinking to themselves, вҖңWho's this young childВҰ38424 going to turn out to be?вҖқ
\s1 Zacharias' prophecy about Yohan
\rem /s1 Zechariah's Song; Zechariah's Prophecy
\p
\v 67 ThenВҰ38434 the boy's fatherВҰ38437, ZachariasВҰ38435, became filledВҰ38439 with the holy \nd spiritВҰ38440\nd* andВҰ38442 prophesiedВҰ38443,
\q1
\v 68 вҖңBlessedВҰ38446 is Yisrael'sВҰ38451 \nd GodВҰ38449 YahwehВҰ38447\nd*,
\q1 becauseВҰ38452 he visitedВҰ38453 us and made a way for hisВҰ38461 peopleВҰ38459 to be freed from slavery.
\q1
\v 69 He brought us a voice that would lead to our salvationВҰ38465,
\q1 us citizens of \add the nation of King\add* DavidВҰ38470, hisВҰ38473 servantВҰ38472
\q1
\v 70 (as he spokeВҰ38475 via the mouthsВҰ38477 of hisВҰ38486 holy prophetsВҰ38485 through the age\add s\add*).
\q1
\v 71 He saved us from ourВҰ38492 enemiesВҰ38491,
\q1 and from the power of all the ones hatingВҰ38498 us,
\q1
\v 72 to show mercyВҰ38501 to ourВҰ38505 ancestorsВҰ38504
\q1 andВҰ38506 to remindВҰ38507 them of hisВҰ38510 holy agreement,
\q1
\v 73 that he had promised AbrahamВҰ38515, ourВҰ38518 ancestor, that he would giveВҰ38520 us.
\q1
\v 74 He rescuedВҰ38528 us from the power of our enemiesВҰ38526,
\q1 so we could serve himВҰ38530 without fear,
\q1
\v 75 committed to obeying himВҰ38536
\q1 for the rest of ourВҰ38545 lives.
\q1
\v 76 \x + \xo 1:76: \xt Mal 3:1.\x*And you too my littleВҰ38549 childВҰ38549, will be calledВҰ38552 a prophetВҰ38550 of the highestВҰ38551 oneвҖ”
\q1 goingВҰ38553 before \nd YahwehВҰ38559\nd* to prepareВҰ38560 hisВҰ38562 paths,
\q1
\v 77 to giveВҰ38564 knowledgeВҰ38565 about salvationВҰ38566 to hisВҰ38569 peopleВҰ38568
\q1 so theirВҰ38574 sinsВҰ38572 can be forgivenВҰ38571
\q1
\v 78 becauseВҰ38576 \nd GodВҰ38579\nd* has compassionВҰ38577 on us and mercyВҰ38578.
\q1 Thus the light from heaven will visitВҰ38584 us
\q1
\v 79 \x + \xo 1:79: \xt Isa 9:2.\x*to shineВҰ38589 on those in darknessВҰ38593 andВҰ38594 sittingВҰ38597 in the shadowВҰ38595 of deathВҰ38596;
\q1 to guide us onto the road of peaceВҰ38605.вҖқ
\p
\v 80 The young boy grew and his spiritВҰ38612 was also strengthenedВҰ38611, and he lived in the wildernessВҰ38617 untilВҰ38618 he started his ministry to \add the people of\add* Yisrael.
\c 2
\s1 Yeshua's birth in Bethlehem
\rem /s1 The Birth of Jesus
\r (Mat. 1:18-25)
\p
\v 1 At that time, CaesarВҰ38634 AugustusВҰ38635 sent a decreeВҰ38632 that everyone throughout the empire needed to registerВҰ38637 \add in a census\add*.
\v 2 (This census was conducted when Quirinius was the governorВҰ38650 of SyriaВҰ38652.)
\v 3 Everyone had to \add officially\add* registerВҰ38658 in the cityВҰ38667 where they were \add born\add*.
\p
\v 4 Because Yosef was a descendant of \add King\add* David, he left the town of \nd NazarethВҰ38677\nd* in the GalileeВҰ38674 \add region\add* andВҰ38669 wentВҰ38668 down to David's town of BethlehemВҰ38689 in YudeaВҰ38681
\v 5 to registerВҰ38699 along with MariaВҰ38702, his pregnantВҰ38710 fiancГ©e.
\v 6 While they were in Bethlehem, the timeВҰ38725 came for herВҰ38735 to give birth
\v 7 and so Maria bore herВҰ38740 firstВҰ38742 son and wrapped him in strips of cloth and slept him in an \add empty\add* feeding trough, becauseВҰ38753 they had missed out on the guestВҰ38760 roomВҰ38760.
\s1 The shepherds and the messengers
\rem /s1 The Shepherds and the Angels
\p
\v 8 In that sameВҰ38770 area, there were some shepherdsВҰ38762 staying out in the fieldsВҰ38772 where they kept watchВҰ38776 over theirВҰ38782 flocksВҰ38781 at nightВҰ38778.
\v 9 A messengerВҰ38785 sent by \nd Yahweh\nd* approachedВҰ38787 them, and \nd Yahweh's\nd* radiance shone aroundВҰ38793 them, and theyВҰ38798 were very frightened.
\v 10 вҖңDon't be scared,вҖқ the messengerВҰ38806 told them, вҖңbecauseВҰ38810 I'm bringing youВҰ38812 a goodВҰ38811 messageВҰ38811 thatВҰ38815 will bring greatВҰ38814 happiness to all peopleВҰ38821
\v 11 becauseВҰ38822 a saviourВҰ38826 for all people was born todayВҰ38825 in David's town. He's the \nd messiahВҰ38829\nd*, \nd YahwehВҰ38830\nd*,
\v 12 and this is how you'll know him: you'll find a baby wrapped in strips of cloth and sleeping in a feeding trough.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ38851 suddenlyВҰ38852 lots of heavenlyВҰ38859 soldiers joined the messengerВҰ38856, praisingВҰ38861 \nd GodВҰ38864\nd* andВҰ38865 sayingВҰ38866,
\v 14 вҖңLet all honour be given to \nd GodВҰ38870\nd* in the highestВҰ38869, andВҰ38871 peaceВҰ38874 on earthВҰ38873 to all people along with goodВҰ38879 will.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ38880 as the messengersВҰ38892 left them andВҰ38907 wentВҰ38883 \add up\add* into the sky, the shepherdsВҰ38897 said to each other, вҖңWell, we'll certainly go into BethlehemВҰ38906 so we can seeВҰ38908 what this was about thatВҰ38914 \nd YahwehВҰ38916\nd* has let us know about.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 SoВҰ38919 they hurriedВҰ38921 \add into town\add* and asked around to find MariaВҰ38928 and YosefВҰ38931, and \add also\add* the baby sleeping in the feeding trough.
\v 17 \add вүҲWhen they met them\add*, they explained what they'd been told about the young baby.
\v 18 Everyone who heardВҰ38956 this was amazed at what the shepherdsВҰ38965 told them,
\v 19 butВҰ38969 MariaВҰ38970 treasuredВҰ38972 all of theseВҰ38976 messagesВҰ38975 in herВҰ38982 heartВҰ38980 and \add often\add* thought about them.
\v 20 Finally the shepherdsВҰ38987 returnedВҰ38985 \add back to their fields\add*вҖ”they were worshipping and praisingВҰ38990 \nd GodВҰ38992\nd* for what they'd heardВҰ38996 and how they'd seen it exactly like they'd been told.
\s1 The child is named Yeshua
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Presented in the Temple; Jesus Is Named
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 2:21: a \xt Lev 12:3; \xo b \xt Luk 1:31.\x*When the baby was eightВҰ39010 daysВҰ39008 old andВҰ39003 hence the timeВҰ39030 for hisВҰ39021 circumcisionВҰ39012, he was given the nameВҰ39020 \nd Yeshua\nd* as instructed by \add God's\add* messengerВҰ39028 even beforeВҰ39029 he was conceivedВҰ39031 in the womb.
\s1 Yeshua is dedicated in the temple
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Presented in the Temple
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ39038 when the time of the \add mother's\add* purificationВҰ39044 was fulfilledВҰ39040 as per Mosheh's instructions, theyВҰ39052 took himВҰ39053 down to Yerushalem to be dedicated to \nd YahwehВҰ39059\nd*
\v 23 \x + \xo 2:23: \xt Exo 13:2,12.\x*to follow what is writtenВҰ39061 in Yahweh's law: EveryВҰ39067 firstborn maleВҰ39068 is set aside for Yahweh
\v 24 \x + \xo 2:22-24: \xt Lev 12:6-8.\x*andВҰ39076 hence a sacrificeВҰ39079 has to be made, whichВҰ39077 accordingВҰ39080 to thatВҰ39077 law is a pair of turtledovesВҰ39088 or a pair of youngВҰ39091 dovesВҰ39092.
\rem /s1 The Prophecy of Simeon
\p
\v 25 Now listen, there was a man named SimeonВҰ39103 in Yerushalem and he was godlyВҰ39111 and committed, waitingВҰ39112 for God to rescue Yisrael. He was \add full\add* of the holy \nd spiritВҰ39117\nd*
\v 26 andВҰ39123 the \nd spiritВҰ39132\nd* had told him that he wouldn't die without seeing Yahweh's \nd messiahВҰ39144\nd*.
\v 27 He had come to the templeВҰ39153 listening to the \nd spiritВҰ39150\nd* at just the same timeВҰ39156 as the parents brought in the baby \nd Yeshua\nd* in order to follow the rituals for new parents.
\v 28 Simeon took the baby into his arms and blessedВҰ39185 \nd GodВҰ39187\nd* and saidВҰ39189,
\v 29 вҖңNow, YahwehВҰ39195, you can send yourВҰ39194 slaveВҰ39193 away in peaceВҰ39201 as you promised
\v 30 becauseВҰ39202 I've set myВҰ39206 eyesВҰ39205 on yourВҰ39209 salvationВҰ39208
\v 31 whichВҰ39210 youВҰ39211 have preparedВҰ39211 in front of everyone:
