\c 5
\s1 Yeshua's power over creation
\rem /s1 The Calling of the First Disciples; Jesus Calls the First Disciples
\r (Mark 1:16-20; Mat. 4:18-22)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 5:1-3: \xt Mrk 3:9-10; 4:1; Mat 13:1-2.\x*One timeВҰ41383 when the crowdВҰ41386 was pressuring Yeshua that they wanted to hearВҰ41391 God's messageВҰ41393 as he stoodВҰ41399 by Lake Galilee,
\v 2 he saw two boats at the edge of the water, but the fishermenВҰ41418 had left the boats so they could wash their nets.
\v 3 Yeshua hopped into one of the boatsВҰ41433 whichВҰ41435 turned out to be Simon's, and askedВҰ41439 himВҰ41440 just to \add row\add* out a littleВҰ41447 way from the land. ThenВҰ41429 Yeshua satВҰ41452 there in the boatВҰ41459 and taughtВҰ41454 the crowdsВҰ41463 from there.
\p
\v 4 Once he'd finished his speakingВҰ41468, he told SimonВҰ41472, вҖң\wj Go out to the deeper parts andВҰ41466 lowerВҰ41479 yourВҰ41483 netsВҰ41482 to catchВҰ41485 \+add some fish\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \x + \xo 5:5: \xt Yhn 21:3.\x*вҖңMasterВҰ41496,вҖқ SimonВҰ41490 answeredВҰ41487, вҖңweВҰ41503 worked all throughВҰ41497 the nightВҰ41500 and didn't catch anything, butВҰ41505 ok, I'll do what youВҰ41509 say and lowerВҰ41515 the netsВҰ41519.вҖқ
\v 6 \x + \xo 5:6: \xt Yhn 21:6.\x*When they lowered the nets, they \add quickly\add* netted a hugeВҰ41528 catch of fish, so much so that theirВҰ41539 nets began to rip
\v 7 and they \add had to\add* signalВҰ41541 to their companionsВҰ41545 in the otherВҰ41549 boatВҰ41550 to comeВҰ41553 and helpВҰ41555. When they got there, they filledВҰ41563 both boatsВҰ41568 \add with so many fish thatВҰ41551 the weight\add* began to sink them.
\v 8 When SimonВҰ41579 PeterВҰ41580 \add had a moment\add* to realise what had just happened, he knelt \add in the boat\add* in front of \nd Yeshua\nd* and said, вҖңYou must leave me, \nd masterВҰ41597\nd*, becauseВҰ41593 I'm just a sinfulВҰ41595 manВҰ41594.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Peter and all those with him were stunned at the size of the catchВҰ41611,
\v 10 including Yacob andВҰ41638 Yohan (Zebedee'sВҰ41631 sonsВҰ41630) who were his \add fishing\add* partnersВҰ41634. ThenВҰ41638 Yeshua told SimonВҰ41636, вҖңDon't be afraidвҖ”from now on you'll be catchingВҰ41656 peopleВҰ41654.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 When they got the boatsВҰ41671 up onto the shore, they left everything there andВҰ41667 followedВҰ41684 afterВҰ41685 Yeshua.
\s1 Yeshua heals a man with leprosy
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Man with Leprosy; The Man With Leprosy; Jesus Cleanses a Leper
\r (Mark 1:40-45; Mat. 8:1-4)
\p
\v 12 In one of the towns that they visited, a manВҰ41698 covered in leprousВҰ41700 \add lesions\add* lay faceВҰ41710 down in front of \nd Yeshua\nd* when he saw him, andВҰ41686 implored him, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ41714\nd*, if you wanted you'd be able to heal me.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 Yeshua reached out his handВҰ41725 andВҰ41720 touchedВҰ41727 him, sayingВҰ41730, вҖңI do want it. Be free from this.вҖқ Immediately the man was clear of leprosyВҰ41737.
\v 14 \x + \xo 5:14: \xt Lev 14:1-32.\x*вҖң\wj Don't tell others,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua instructedВҰ41744, вҖң\wj but go directly to the priestВҰ41756 with the offeringВҰ41758 commanded by Mosheh and show yourselfВҰ41754 to himВҰ41745 \+add for clearance\+add* and as a testimonyВҰ41769 to them.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 15 However the news about Yeshua was spreading all around, and large crowdsВҰ41816 were gathering to listen to himВҰ41813 and to be healedВҰ41820 from theirВҰ41827 diseases,
\v 16 butВҰ41829 then he would \add regularly\add* withdrawВҰ41831 into the wildernessВҰ41834 to pray.
\s1 A paralysed man is lowered through the roof
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Paralysed Man; Jesus Heals a Paralytic
\r (Mark 2:1-12; Mat. 9:1-8)
\p
\v 17 Yeshua was teaching one day, and some from the Pharisee partyВҰ41855 and some religious teachersВҰ41859 were sittingВҰ41851 there \add listening\add*. They had comeВҰ41865 from villagesВҰ41869 all around GalileeВҰ41872 and YudeaВҰ41874, and also from Yerushalem, and the powerВҰ41878 of \nd YahwehВҰ41879\nd* was there enabling Yeshua to heal people.
\v 18 ThenВҰ41887, look, some menВҰ41889 turned up carryingВҰ41890 a paralysedВҰ41898 manВҰ41894 on a stretcher, and they tried to bring him inside and place him in front of Yeshua
\v 19 but becauseВҰ41917 of the crowdВҰ41919 they couldn't find a wayВҰ41914 in. SoВҰ41910 instead, they went \add up the stairs\add* to the \add flat\add* roof andВҰ41910 removed some tilesВҰ41930 in order to let the stretcherВҰ41940 down right in front of \nd YeshuaВҰ41948\nd*.
\v 20 When he saw theirВҰ41956 faithВҰ41955, he saidВҰ41957, вҖңMan, yourВҰ41968 sinsВҰ41967 have been forgivenВҰ41963.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖңWho's this guy who's insulting God?вҖқ the teachersВҰ41973 andВҰ41974 Pharisees started to say among themselves. вҖңOnly \em God\em* is able to forgiveВҰ41991 sinsВҰ41992.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 But \nd Yeshua\nd* knew what they were thinkingВҰ42014 and saying, and answeredВҰ42007 them, вҖң\wj Why are you reasoningВҰ42014 about this in yourВҰ42018 minds?\wj*
\v 23 \wj WhichВҰ42020 is easierВҰ42022 to say: вҖҳYourВҰ42029 sinsВҰ42028 have been forgivenВҰ42024,вҖҷ or вҖҳStand up and walkВҰ42035вҖҷ?\wj*
\v 24 \wj But I'll demonstrate to you that humanity's child \+em does\+em* have the authorityВҰ42047 to forgiveВҰ42052 sinsВҰ42053 here on earthВҰ42051.\wj*вҖқ Then he turned to the paralysedВҰ42059 manВҰ42046 and told him, вҖңListen to me. Stand up and pick up yourВҰ42071 stretcherВҰ42069, then go home.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 Immediately the man stoodВҰ42080 up, right there in front of them all, picked up what he'd been lyingВҰ42090 on, andВҰ42078 headed off to hisВҰ42096 homeВҰ42095 praising \nd GodВҰ42099\nd*.
\v 26 Everyone was astounded and they too praisedВҰ42105 \nd GodВҰ42107\nd*. ButВҰ42100 there was also a feeling of fearВҰ42110 and they said, вҖңWe'veВҰ42118 witnessed something out-of-the-normal todayВҰ42120!вҖқ
\s1 Levi follows Yeshua and hosts a banquet
\rem /s1 The Calling of Levi; Jesus Calls Levi (Matthew)
\r (Mark 2:13-17; Mat. 9:9-13)
\p
\v 27 Yeshua wentВҰ42125 outside after that and he sawВҰ42139 a tax-collector named LeviВҰ42142 sittingВҰ42147 in his officeВҰ42150 and told him, вҖң\wj Come and followВҰ42155 me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 28 SoВҰ42157 Levi left everything and went and followedВҰ42166 Yeshua.
\p
\v 29 ThenВҰ42168 LeviВҰ42175 prepared a large meal in hisВҰ42182 home for Yeshua, plus thereВҰ42184 were also a lot of tax-collectors andВҰ42168 othersВҰ42191 who were sittingВҰ42197 with them.
\v 30 \x + \xo 5:30: \xt Luk 15:1-2.\x*Some from the Pharisees partyВҰ42202 and religiousВҰ42207 teachersВҰ42207 grumbledВҰ42200 at Yeshua's followers, complaining, вҖңWhy are you all eatingВҰ42224 and drinkingВҰ42227 with taxВҰ42221 collectorsВҰ42221 and other low-life?вҖқ
\p
\v 31 ButВҰ42229 it was \nd Yeshua\nd* who answeredВҰ42230, вҖң\wj Healthy people don'tВҰ42238 need a doctorВҰ42243вҖ”only those who are sickВҰ42246.\wj*
\v 32 \wj I didn'tВҰ42248 come to call those who are вҖҳrighteousВҰ42252вҖҷ, but to call sinnersВҰ42255 to come and turn away from disobeying God.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The question about fasting
\rem /s1 Jesus Questioned About Fasting; A Discussion about Fasting; The Question about Fasting
\r (Mark 2:18-22; Mat. 9:14-17)
\p
\v 33 ThenВҰ42259 the religious leaders complained, вҖңYohan's followers often fast and bring their needs to God, as do the Pharisees, but your followers are eatingВҰ42290 and drinkingВҰ42292.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj You can'tВҰ42301 make the groomsmen fast at a wedding,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ42298, вҖң\wj not while the groom is with them.\wj*
\v 35 \wj But yes, there will be a future time when the groom will be takenВҰ42331 away from them, and then they'll fast.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ42344 he went on to tell them this parableВҰ42346, вҖң\wj No one repairs their old clothes by puttingВҰ42357 on a patch of new material. If they did, the new patch will likely tear off again, plus it wouldn't look right anyway.\wj*
\v 37 \wj Similarly, no one puts new wine \+add to mature\+add* into old wineskins. If they did, the new wine would certainly burstВҰ42395 the old wineskin and it would all pour out and the wineskin would be ruined as well.\wj*
\v 38 \wj New wine needs to be put into a new wineskinВҰ42418.\wj*
\v 39 \wj And no one who's \+add used to\+add* the old \+add ways\+add* wants the new, becauseВҰ42435 he'll claim that the old is goodВҰ42438 \+add enough\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\c 6
\s1 Master of the Rest Day
\rem /s1 The Question about the Sabbath; A Discussion about the Sabbath; Lord of the Sabbath
\r (Mark 2:23-28; Mat. 12:1-8)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 6:1: \xt Deu 23:25.\x*One Rest Day, Yeshua was walking through some fields of grain and hisВҰ42460 followers were pluckingВҰ42455 the headsВҰ42466 of grain and rubbingВҰ42469 them \add apart\add* in theirВҰ42470 handsВҰ42471, thenВҰ42443 chewing the grains.
\v 2 But some from the Pharisees partyВҰ42477 asked, вҖңWhy are youВҰ42484 doingВҰ42484 that? It's prohibited \add to harvest\add* on a Rest Day.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖң\wj Haven't you read about DavidВҰ42516,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ42499, вҖң\wj when himВҰ42525 and his men were hungry and what they did?\wj*
\v 4 \x + \xo 6:4: \xt Lev 24:9.\x*вҖң\wj He wentВҰ42529 into God's temple and took the вҖҳbreadВҰ42538 of the presenceВҰ42541вҖҷ and ateВҰ42545 some and gaveВҰ42547 some to his men, even though it's only priestsВҰ42565 that are allowed to eatВҰ42558 that.\wj*вҖқ
\v 5 ThenВҰ42595 he added, вҖң\wj Humanity's child is the \+nd masterВҰ42599\+nd* of the rest days.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua heals the deformed hand
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals on the Sabbath; The Man with a Withered Hand; The Man with a Paralysed Hand
\r (Mark 3:1-6; Mat. 12:9-14)
\p
\v 6 On a different Rest Day, Yeshua went into a meetingВҰ42624 hallВҰ42624 andВҰ42611 was teachingВҰ42627 \add the congregation\add*. There was a manВҰ42633 thereВҰ42634 with a deformedВҰ42647 rightВҰ42644 handВҰ42640
\v 7 and the religiousВҰ42653 teachersВҰ42653 and Pharisees were watchingВҰ42649 Yeshua closelyВҰ42649 to see if he might heal the man on the Rest Day so they'd have something to accuseВҰ42665 him of.
\v 8 ButВҰ42704 he knew theirВҰ42676 plans and spoke to the man with the deformedВҰ42686 handВҰ42690, вҖң\wj Stand up and come into the middle.\wj*вҖқ SoВҰ42704 the man gotВҰ42706 up and stoodВҰ42707 in front of them.
\v 9 вҖң\wj I want to ask all of youВҰ42720,\wj*вҖқ saidВҰ42709 \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\wj whetherВҰ42722 or not it's allowable to do goodВҰ42728 on the Rest Day, or only evilВҰ42730вҖ”to saveВҰ42732 lifeВҰ42731 or to destroyВҰ42735 it?\wj*вҖқ
\v 10 Turning \add slowly\add* and looking at them all, he thenВҰ42739 said to the man, вҖң\wj Hold out yourВҰ42754 hand.\wj*вҖқ The man did it and hisВҰ42766 hand was healed,
\v 11 butВҰ42773 the religious leaders were mad with anger and discussedВҰ42779 among themselves about what they could do to \nd YeshuaВҰ42791\nd*.
\s1 Yeshua chooses twelve to be missionaries
\rem /s1 Jesus Chooses the Twelve Apostles
\r (Mark 3:13-19; Mat. 10:1-4)
\p
\v 12 One day Yeshua climbed a hill to pray, andВҰ42793 thenВҰ42793 he spent the nightВҰ42810 there praying to \nd GodВҰ42816\nd*.
\v 13 In the morning, he called together hisВҰ42825 followers, andВҰ42817 choseВҰ42827 twelveВҰ42830 of them that he thenВҰ42817 called вҖҳmissionariesвҖҷ:
\v 14 Simon (who he also namedВҰ42841 PeterВҰ42842) and hisВҰ42850 brotherВҰ42848 AndrewВҰ42845, Yacob and Yohan, PhilipВҰ42866 and BartholomewВҰ42868,
\v 15 MatthewВҰ42870 and ThomasВҰ42872, Yacob (Alfaeus' son), SimonВҰ42882 (the one known as a Zealot),
\v 16 Yudas (son of Yacob), and Yudas IscariotВҰ42891 (who eventually betrayedВҰ42895 him).
\s1 The crowds want to touch Yeshua
\rem /s1 Jesus Teaches and Heals; Blessings and Woes; Crowds Follow Jesus
\r (Mat. 4:23-25)
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ42896 coming down the hill with them, Yeshua stoodВҰ42900 on a flat area along with a large crowdВҰ42905 of hisВҰ42908 followers. There was also a large number of peopleВҰ42913 from all around YudeaВҰ42917 and Yerushalem and from the coastalВҰ42927 areas of TyreВҰ42928 and Tsidon
\v 18 who cameВҰ42932 to hear what he had to say, as well as getting healed from theirВҰ42941 various diseasesВҰ42940.
\v 19 All the people in the crowdВҰ42955 wanted to touchВҰ42958 him, becauseВҰ42961 powerВҰ42962 would come out from him andВҰ42952 he was healingВҰ42967 everyone.
\s1 The blessed and the unblessed
\rem /s1 Blessings and Woes; Jesus's sermon to the disciples; The Beatitudes; Happiness and Sorrow
\r (Mat. 5:1-12)
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ42969 looking up at hisВҰ42976 followers, he said,
\q1 вҖң\wj BlessedВҰ42982 are the poor, becauseВҰ42985 God's kingdomВҰ42990 is yoursВҰ42986.\wj*
\q1
\v 21 \wj Blessed are those who don't have enough to eat now, because you'll all be satisfiedВҰ42998.\wj*
\q1 \wj Blessed are those who are weepingВҰ43002 now, because you'll all be laughingВҰ43005.\wj*
\p
\v 22 \x + \xo 6:22: \xt 1Pe 4:14.\x*\wj You'reВҰ43035 all blessed when peopleВҰ43015 hateВҰ43011 you and snub you, and when they derideВҰ43021 you and slander yourВҰ43028 reputations as evilВҰ43030, all on accountВҰ43031 of humanity's child.\wj*
\v 23 \x + \xo 6:23: \xt 2Ch 36:16; Acts 7:52.\x*\wj Be happy at that time andВҰ43043 dance with happiness, becauseВҰ43046 you'll have a large rewardВҰ43050 in heavenВҰ43057. TheirВҰ43069 ancestorsВҰ43068 did the sameВҰ43062 sorts of things to the prophetsВҰ43066.\wj*
\q1
\rem /s1 Sorrows Foretold
\v 24 \wj HoweverВҰ43070 it's tragic for all you rich people, becauseВҰ43075 you've already enjoyed all those comfortsВҰ43078.\wj*
\q1
\v 25 \wj It's tragic for all of you who are full now, because you'll all be hungry.\wj*
\q1 \wj It's tragic for all of you who are laughingВҰ43090 now, because you'll all be mourningВҰ43093 and crying.\wj*
\q1
\v 26 \wj It's tragic for you wheneverВҰ43098 all the peopleВҰ43107 say they admire you, because theirВҰ43119 ancestorsВҰ43118 did the sameВҰ43112 to the falseВҰ43116 prophetsВҰ43116.\wj*
\s1 Loving the unlovely
\rem /s1 Love for Enemies
\r (Mat. 5:38-48; 7:12a)
\p
\v 27 вҖң\wj But I'll tell all of you who are listening: Love yourВҰ43129 enemiesВҰ43128 and be kind to those who hate you.\wj*
\v 28 \wj Give a blessingВҰ43136 to those who curse you and pray for those who mistreatВҰ43146 you.\wj*
\v 29 \wj When someone slaps you on the face, offer them the otherВҰ43161 side, and when someone forces you to hand over your coatВҰ43168, don'tВҰ43173 resist if they want your shirt as well.\wj*
\v 30 \wj Give to everyoneВҰ43175 who asks youВҰ43179 for something, andВҰ43181 when someone takes yourВҰ43186 stuff, don'tВҰ43187 go demandingВҰ43188 itВҰ43188 back.\wj*
\v 31 \x + \xo 6:31: \xt Mat 7:12.\x*\wj However you'd all like peopleВҰ43199 to treat you, that's how you should be treating them.\wj*
\p
\v 32 вҖң\wj And if you only love those who love you, how good is that? Even those who disobey God love those who love them.\wj*
\v 33 \wj If you only do good things to people who are good to you, how good is that? Even those who disobey God do that.\wj*
\v 34 \wj And if you only lend \+add money\+add* to people that you're expecting to \+add repay\+add* you, how good is that? Even those who disobey God lend to others like them, knowing they'll get their money back.\wj*
\v 35 \wj Instead, you all should love your enemiesВҰ43277 and do good and lend out even when you expectВҰ43285 to get nothingВҰ43283 back. Then your rewardВҰ43289 will be large and you'll all be children of the highestВҰ43300 \+add God\+add* becauseВҰ43301 he is good to ungratefulВҰ43308 and evilВҰ43310 \+add people\+add*.\wj*
\v 36 \wj You should be compassionate towards others, because yourВҰ43319 fatherВҰ43318 is compassionate.\wj*
\s1 Don't judge others
\rem /s1 Judging Others; Don't Condemn Others
\r (Mat. 7:1-5)
\p
\v 37 вҖң\wj Don't judge others, then you definitely won't be judgedВҰ43331. Don't condemn others, then you definitely won't be condemned.\wj*
\v 38 \wj Give to others, and then you'll be givenВҰ43348 to generously. The returned amount will be really packed in to the container and even overflowingВҰ43358, becauseВҰ43366 however you measure things out for others, that's how things will be measured out for you.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 39 \x + \xo 6:39: \xt Mat 15:14.\x*ThenВҰ43377 Yeshua told them a parableВҰ43379: вҖң\wj SurelyВҰ43381 a blind person can'tВҰ43381 be a guide for someone else who's blind. Won't both of them fall into a ditch?\wj*
\v 40 \x + \xo 6:40: \xt Yhn 13:16; 15:20; Mat 10:24-25.\x*\wj An apprenticeВҰ43396 isn'tВҰ43394 aboveВҰ43397 their teacher, but can become like their teacher once they're fully trained.\wj*
\p
\v 41 вҖң\wj How come you notice the speckВҰ43414 in someone else's eye, yet don'tВҰ43431 even notice the log that's in yourВҰ43421 own eye?\wj*
\v 42 \wj How can you tell that person, вҖҳHey, let me get that speck out of your eye,вҖҷ when you can'tВҰ43466 even see the log in \+em your\+em* eye? You hypocrite, get the log out of your eye and then you'll be able to see clearlyВҰ43481 so you can remove the speck in the other person's eye.\wj*
\s1 The tree is recognised by its fruit
\rem /s1 A Tree and Its Fruit
\r (Mat. 7:16-20; 12:33-35)
\p
\v 43 вҖң\wj A good tree doesn't produce bad fruit, and a bad tree doesn't produce good fruit,\wj*
\v 44 \x + \xo 6:44: \xt Mat 12:33.\x*\wj but each treeВҰ43519 is recognised by the fruitВҰ43524 it produces. You don'tВҰ43529 pick figsВҰ43536 from thistles or pick grapesВҰ43542 from thornВҰ43533 bushes.\wj*
\v 45 \x + \xo 6:45: \xt Mat 12:34.\x*\wj A good person produces good deeds as a result of all the good things inside them, and an evil person produces evil deeds as a result of the evil \+add inside\+add*, becauseВҰ43574 what comes out of your mouthВҰ43582 originates in your mindВҰ43553.\wj*
\s1 The two house-builders
\rem /s1 The Wise and Foolish Builders; The Two Foundations; The Two House Builders; Building on a Solid Foundation
\r (Mat. 7:24-27)
\p
\v 46 вҖң\wj SoВҰ43586 why do you all call me вҖҳmaster, master,вҖҷ yet you don'tВҰ43593 do what I say?\wj*
\v 47 \wj EveryoneВҰ43598 who comes to me and listens to myВҰ43605 messagesВҰ43608 and puts them into practice, I'll show youВҰ43615 who that person is like:\wj*
\v 48 \wj That person is like a man buildingВҰ43622 a house. He dug and drilled and laid a foundationВҰ43630 on the rock, and then when there was a flood that dashedВҰ43637 againstВҰ43637 that house, it didn'tВҰ43644 shakeВҰ43646 it becauseВҰ43648 it was builtВҰ43652 well.\wj*
\v 49 \wj But the person who listens \add вүҲbutВҰ43660\add* doesn't put the message into practice is like a man thatВҰ43678 just builtВҰ43668 his house on the groundВҰ43674 with no foundationВҰ43676, and when the floodВҰ43683 dashedВҰ43679 againstВҰ43679 it, the house immediatelyВҰ43685 collapsed and broke into many pieces.\wj*вҖқ
\c 7
\s1 Yeshua heals the centurion's slave
\rem /s1 Miracles and parables; Jesus Heals a Centurion's Servant; Jesus Heals a Roman Officer's Servant; Faith of the Roman Officer; The Faith of the Centurion
\r (Mat. 8:5-13)
\p
\v 1 AfterВҰ43697 Yeshua had finished sharing those messagesВҰ43707 with the peopleВҰ43714, he entered \add the town of\add* CapernaumВҰ43718.
\v 2 A Roman army commander there had a slaveВҰ43723 that he valued, but who was sickВҰ43725 andВҰ43720 expected to die.
\v 3 He had heardВҰ43735 aboutВҰ43737 Yeshua, so he asked the \add local\add* Jewish eldersВҰ43743 to talk to Yeshua on his behalf andВҰ43736 to ask him to comeВҰ43751 to heal his slaveВҰ43754.
\v 4 When the elders got to \nd Yeshua\nd*, they earnestlyВҰ43766 imploredВҰ43763 himВҰ43765 sayingВҰ43767, вҖңThe man you'd be helping is worthВҰ43770 it
\v 5 becauseВҰ43778 he loves us Jews and he builtВҰ43787 the \add local\add* meetingВҰ43784 hallВҰ43784 for us.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ43790 \nd Yeshua\nd* went with them but as they got closer to the houseВҰ43810, the commander had sentВҰ43811 some friendsВҰ43819 to tell him, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ43823\nd*, don'tВҰ43803 troubleВҰ43825 yourself becauseВҰ43827 I'm not worthyВҰ43829 enough to have you enter myВҰ43836 home
\v 7 and that's why I never came to youВҰ43843 personally. However, just issue a command and then myВҰ43854 boy will be healedВҰ43851
\v 8 becauseВҰ43856 I'm appointedВҰ43862 under authorityВҰ43861 and have otherВҰ43875 soldiersВҰ43866 under me. When I tell one of them to go, he goes, and when I tell one to come, he comes, and when I tell myВҰ43882 slaveВҰ43881 to do something, he does it.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 When he heardВҰ43887 that, \nd Yeshua\nd* was amazed and turnedВҰ43896 to face the crowdВҰ43901 that was followingВҰ43899 him and saidВҰ43902, вҖң\wj I can tell you that never before in all of Yisrael have I encountered so much faithВҰ43914!\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 10 By the time that the \add commander's friends\add* had gotten back to the houseВҰ43926, they foundВҰ43930 that the slaveВҰ43933 was already well again.
\s1 Yeshua brings the widow's son back to life
\rem /s1 Jesus Raises the Widow's Son at Nain; Jesus Raises a Widow's Son
\p
\v 11 The next dayВҰ43938, Yeshua went to a town calledВҰ43945 NainВҰ43946, andВҰ43935 hisВҰ43952 followers went with him as well as a large crowdВҰ43955 of people.
\v 12 As he got near the town gateВҰ43964, look, a dead boy was beingВҰ43969 carriedВҰ43969 out \add to the cemetery\add*. The motherВҰ43975 was now a widowВҰ43980 and he had been their only son, and a large number of the local residents were with her.
\v 13 When he saw her, the \nd masterВҰ43998\nd* felt sorry for her andВҰ43992 saidВҰ44004, вҖң\wj Don't cry.\wj*вҖқ
\v 14 Then he went up closer and touchedВҰ44010 the coffinВҰ44012, and the pallbearers stoppedВҰ44016. Then he spoke, вҖң\wj YoungВҰ44019 manВҰ44019, I'm talkingВҰ44022 to you: get up.\wj*вҖқ
\v 15 The deadВҰ44028 son satВҰ44026 up and started talkingВҰ44031, and Yeshua led him to hisВҰ44038 motherВҰ44037.
\v 16 Everyone felt a bit apprehensive and theyВҰ44045 praisedВҰ44045 God sayingВҰ44048, вҖңA powerful prophetВҰ44050 appeared amongВҰ44055 us,вҖқ and вҖңGod has been here with hisВҰ44064 peopleВҰ44063.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ44065 the news about Yeshua spread all around YudeaВҰ44074 andВҰ44077 all the surroundingВҰ44081 area.
\s1 Yohan checks out the messiah
\rem /s1 Jesus and John the Baptist; The Messengers from John the Baptist
\r (Mat. 11:2-19)
\p
\v 18 The apprentices of Yohan-the-immerser reportedВҰ44087 all theseВҰ44098 things back to him andВҰ44084 he choose twoВҰ44102 of hisВҰ44095 apprentices
\v 19 and sentВҰ44109 them to \nd Yeshua\nd* to ask, вҖңAre youВҰ44119 the promised one, or should weВҰ44126 wait for someone else?вҖқ
\p
\v 20 SoВҰ44129 when they got to Yeshua, the two menВҰ44133 told himВҰ44131, вҖңYohan-the-immerser sentВҰ44141 us here to ask you if you're the promised one, or should we wait for someone else?вҖқ
\p
\v 21 While they were still there, he healedВҰ44161 many people from their diseasesВҰ44165 and difficulties, as well as evilВҰ44172 spiritsВҰ44170 and some blindВҰ44174 people being able to see again,
\v 22 \x + \xo 7:22: a \xt Isa 35:5-6; \xo b \xt Isa 61:1.\x*so thenВҰ44181 heВҰ44185 answeredВҰ44182 them, вҖң\wj Go and tell Yohan everything that you've seen and heardВҰ44199 here: how blindВҰ44205 people can see again, lame people are walkingВҰ44209 now, people with leprosy are clear, some deadВҰ44215 have come back to life, and the goodВҰ44219 messageВҰ44219 is being preachedВҰ44219 to the poor.\wj*
\v 23 \wj God will blessВҰ44221 those who don'tВҰ44226 misjudge me.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 24 When Yohan's messengersВҰ44233 had leftВҰ44250, Yeshua started asking the crowdsВҰ44243 about Yohan, вҖң\wj What did youВҰ44250 all go out into the wildernessВҰ44253 to seeВҰ44254? A reed waving in the windВҰ44258?\wj*
\v 25 \wj Yes, butВҰ44261 what did youВҰ44264 all go out to seeВҰ44265? A manВҰ44266 dressedВҰ44270 in fine clothes? Well, those in nice clothes andВҰ44276 living in luxuryВҰ44277 are in fine homes.\wj*
\v 26 \wj So what was it that you wentВҰ44287 out to seeВҰ44288? A prophet? Yes, I'll tell you that he is more importantВҰ44294 than \+add any old\+add* prophet.\wj*
\v 27 \x + \xo 7:27: \xt Mal 3:1.\x*\wj He is the one that was writtenВҰ44310 about: вҖҳSeeВҰ44311, I'm sendingВҰ44313 myВҰ44316 messengerВҰ44315 ahead of you and he will prepareВҰ44321 yourВҰ44319 pathВҰ44323 before you get there.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 28 \wj I'm telling all of youВҰ44331, no one who's been born from a woman is greater than Yohan, yet the lowest person in God's kingdomВҰ44353 is greater than him.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 7:29-30: \xt Mat 21:32; Luk 3:12.\x*(When all the peopleВҰ44362 andВҰ44364 the tax-collectors that had been immersedВҰ44370 by Yohan heardВҰ44363 that, theyВҰ44367 concurred that God's way is fair,
\v 30 however the Pharisees andВҰ44377 the lawyersВҰ44379 who had not been immersedВҰ44389 by himВҰ44391, they rejectedВҰ44384 God's plan for them.)
\p
\v 31 вҖң\wj SoВҰ44401 what can I compare this generationВҰ44406 with?\wj*вҖқ asked Yeshua. вҖң\wj Who are theyВҰ44410 similarВҰ44411 to?\wj*
\v 32 \wj They're like littleВҰ44415 childrenВҰ44415 sittingВҰ44421 in the marketplaceВҰ44419 and callingВҰ44423 out to each other, вҖҳWe played the fluteВҰ44431 for you all but you didn't danceВҰ44435, then we played a sad song but you all didn't weep.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 33 \wj BecauseВҰ44442 Yohan-the-immerser came and he didn't eat breadВҰ44451 or drinkВҰ44455 wine, so you all said that he has a demonВҰ44460.\wj*
\v 34 \wj Then humanity's child came and ate and drank and youВҰ44471 all said, вҖҳLookВҰ44473, he's a gluttonВҰ44475 and a drunkardВҰ44477вҖ”a friendВҰ44478 of tax-collectors and those who disobey God.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 35 \wj ButВҰ44483 wisdomВҰ44486 is justifiedВҰ44484 by all herВҰ44492 childrenВҰ44491.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The woman who anoints Yeshua's feet
\rem /s1 Jesus Anointed by a Sinful Woman; Jesus at the Home of Simon the Pharisee; A Sinful Woman Forgiven
\p
\v 36 Another time, someoneВҰ44497 from the Pharisees party invited Yeshua to go to his place for a meal, and so he went there and reclinedВҰ44516 \add on a flat couch\add*.
\v 37 \x + \xo 7:37-38: \xt Yhn 12:3; Mrk 14:3; Mat 26:7.\x*ThenВҰ44540 wowВҰ44519, a sinful womanВҰ44520 from the cityВҰ44526 who knew that he was recliningВҰ44534 in there, \add came into the room\add* carrying a \add beautiful carved\add* stone flaskВҰ44543 of scented skin-cream.
\v 38 She stoodВҰ44547 weepingВҰ44556 behindВҰ44548 Yeshua's feet, wettingВҰ44560 his feet with her tears. Then she used her hairВҰ44569 to wipe off the tears and kissed his feet and \add rubbed\add* the lotion into them.
\v 39 When the Pharisee who had invitedВҰ44592 Yeshua saw this, he said to himselfВҰ44597, вҖңIf that man was a prophetВҰ44603, he'd know who she is andВҰ44586 what kind of womanВҰ44610 it is that's touchingВҰ44613 him, becauseВҰ44616 she breaks God's laws.вҖқ
\p
\v 40 вҖңSimonВҰ44627,вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* asked him, вҖңI need to tell you somethingВҰ44630.вҖқ
\p вҖңTell me, teacher,вҖқ he replied.
\p
\v 41 \add Then Yeshua told him this story:\add* вҖң\wj Once there were twoВҰ44643 people who had borrowed from a moneyВҰ44646 lender: one borrowed five-hundred coinsВҰ44651 andВҰ44654 the otherВҰ44655 borrowed fiftyВҰ44657.\wj*
\v 42 \wj ButВҰ44660 neither of them was able to repay him, so heВҰ44664 wrote-off both of theirВҰ44667 debts. Now after thatВҰ44665, whichВҰ44665 one of them do you think would appreciate him more?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 43 вҖңI supposeВҰ44681,вҖқ answeredВҰ44675 SimonВҰ44679, вҖңthat it was the one who was forgiven the biggest debt.вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj You're right,\wj*вҖқ said Yeshua.
\v 44 ThenВҰ44695 looking at the woman he said to SimonВҰ44702, вҖң\wj You see this woman? I came into yourВҰ44709 houseВҰ44713 but you didn'tВҰ44725 give me any waterВҰ44716 to wash my feet, yet she wet my feet with her tearsВҰ44731 andВҰ44695 thenВҰ44695 wipedВҰ44742 them off with her hairВҰ44738.\wj*
\v 45 \wj You didn'tВҰ44745 kissВҰ44743 me \+add when I entered\+add*, butВҰ44748 this womanВҰ44747 hasn't stopped kissingВҰ44755 myВҰ44756 feetВҰ44758 since I cameВҰ44751 in.\wj*
\v 46 \wj YouВҰ44760 didn'tВҰ44764 offer oliveВҰ44760 oil for my head, butВҰ44767 she anointed my feetВҰ44772 with this lotion,\wj*
\v 47 \wj so that's why I'll tell you this: HerВҰ44786 many sinsВҰ44785 have been forgiven becauseВҰ44790 she showed a lot of love, but the one who has been forgiven little, is lovingВҰ44799 little.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 48 ThenВҰ44801 he saidВҰ44800 to the woman, вҖң\wj YourВҰ44806 sinsВҰ44808 have been forgivenВҰ44803.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 49 The others who were recliningВҰ44812 in the room started to ask to each other, вҖңWho \add does he think\add* he is to be able to even forgiveВҰ44826 sinsВҰ44825?вҖқ
\p
\v 50 вҖң\wj YourВҰ44835 faithВҰ44834 has savedВҰ44836 you,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua saidВҰ44827 to the womanВҰ44831, вҖң\wj Go in peaceВҰ44841.\wj*вҖқ
\c 8
\s1 The team spreading the good message
\rem /s1 Women Who Followed Jesus; The Parable of the Sower; Women Who Accompanied Jesus; Some Women Accompany Jesus
\p
\v 1 After that, Yeshua started travellingВҰ44851 around all the towns and villagesВҰ44856вҖ”preachingВҰ44859 and sharing the goodВҰ44859 messageВҰ44859 about God's kingdomВҰ44861. His twelveВҰ44866 apprentices were with himВҰ44869
\v 2 \x + \xo 8:2-3: \xt Mrk 15:40-41; Mat 27:55-56; Luk 23:49.\x*along with some womenВҰ44872 who'd been healedВҰ44877 from evilВҰ44881 spiritsВҰ44879 and sicknessesВҰ44883: MariaВҰ44884 from MagdalaВҰ44887 (that sevenВҰ44892 demonsВҰ44891 had comeВҰ44894 out of),
\v 3 YoannaВҰ44896 (who's Chusa'sВҰ44898 wifeВҰ44897 and \add one of King\add* Herod's managersВҰ44899), SusannaВҰ44902, and many othersВҰ44904, who used the group's assets to look after their needs.
\s1 The parable about spreading seeds
\rem /s1 Story of the Farmer Scattering Seed; The Parable of the Sower
\r (Mark 4:1-9; Mat. 13:1-9)
\p
\v 4 A large crowdВҰ44920 gathered around Yeshua, including many who'd travelled out from the cityВҰ44926, andВҰ44919 he told them this parableВҰ44933:
\p
\v 5 вҖң\wj \+add One day\+add* a \+add farmer\+add* wentВҰ44938 out to plant some seeds. As he spread the seeds, some of them fell alongВҰ44956 the pathВҰ44958 where they got trampledВҰ44960 on, andВҰ44947 the birdsВҰ44963 ate them.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Some of the seeds landed in a rocky area where they sproutedВҰ44978, but \+add thenВҰ44969\+add* they witheredВҰ44979 up becauseВҰ44981 they didn'tВҰ44983 have enough moistureВҰ44985.\wj*
\v 7 \wj Some of the seeds landed in a patch of thistles, andВҰ44995 as the plants started to grow, they were chokedВҰ45000 out by the thistles.\wj*
\v 8 \wj Some of the seeds fell onto goodВҰ45013 soil, andВҰ45003 thenВҰ45003 the plants grew up to produceВҰ45020 a harvest of one hundredВҰ45022 times as much.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Purpose of the Parables
\rem /r (Matthew 13.10-17; Mark 4.10-12)
\p As he was sayingВҰ45024 this, he was \add also\add* telling them, вҖң\wj Anyone who wants to hearВҰ45029, listen carefully.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The reason for parables
\r (Mark 4:10-12; Mat. 13:10-17)
\p
\v 9 \add After this,\add* hisВҰ45036 apprenticesВҰ45035 asked him, вҖңWhat'sВҰ45039 that parableВҰ45043 all about?вҖқ
\v 10 \x + \xo 8:10: \xt Isa 6:9 (LXX).\x*вҖң\wj You're permitted to knowВҰ45050 the mysteriesВҰ45053 of God's kingdomВҰ45055,\wj*вҖқ respondedВҰ45047 Yeshua, вҖң\wj but the others get parablesВҰ45063 so that when they look, they won't see, andВҰ45046 when they listen, they won't understandВҰ45075.\wj*
\s1 The meaning of the parable about the seeds
\rem /s1 Jesus Explains the Parable of the Sower; The Parable of the Sower Explained
\r (Mark 4:13-20; Mat. 13:18-23)
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj \+add вүҲSoВҰ45078\+add* this is what the parableВҰ45081 \+add means\+add*: the seeds are God's messageВҰ45086.\wj*
\v 12 \wj The seeds along the road are those who hear \+add the message\+add*, but afterwards the devilВҰ45104 comes along andВҰ45091 snatches the message away from theirВҰ45112 heartsВҰ45111, so that they don'tВҰ45116 believeВҰ45117 or get savedВҰ45118.\wj*
\v 13 \wj The seeds among the rocks are those who happily accept the messageВҰ45133 but don'tВҰ45140 put down any roots, so they believeВҰ45145 for a \+add short\+add* time, andВҰ45120 thenВҰ45120 when temptationsВҰ45149 come, they pull back from \+add God\+add*.\wj*
\v 14 \wj The seeds among the thistles are those who heardВҰ45161 the message but get chokedВҰ45173 underВҰ45163 worriesВҰ45164 and wealth and the good life, and so they never reach maturityВҰ45176.\wj*
\v 15 \wj But the seeds in the good soil are those good \+add people\+add* with good heartsВҰ45191 and after hearing the messageВҰ45197, they follow it, and produceВҰ45202 fruitВҰ45202 from their enduranceВҰ45204.\wj*
\s1 The light will expose what's hidden
\rem /s1 A Lamp on a Stand; A Lamp under a Bowl; A Lamp under a Jar; Illustration of the Lamp
\r (Mark 4:21-25)
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 8:16: \xt Mat 5:15; Luk 11:33.\x*вҖң\wj No one lights a lamp andВҰ45206 thenВҰ45206 puts a coverВҰ45209 over it or puts it under a bed, but rather it's placed on a lampstandВҰ45220 so that everyoneВҰ45205 coming into \+add the room\+add* can see the lightВҰ45229.\wj*
\p
\v 17 \x + \xo 8:17: \xt Mat 10:26; Luk 12:2.\x*вҖң\wj Similarly, nothing is hiddenВҰ45233 that won't eventually become visible, and nothing is secretВҰ45240 that won't become knownВҰ45247 and exposed.\wj*
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 8:18: \xt Mat 25:29; Luk 19:26.\x*вҖң\wj SoВҰ45253 take care in what youВҰ45255 listen to, becauseВҰ45259 anyone who has now, will be givenВҰ45263 more, andВҰ45265 anyone who doesn't have, whatever they think they do have will be takenВҰ45278 away from them.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's mother and siblings
\rem /s1 The True Family of Jesus; Jesus' Mother and Brothers; The True Kindred of Jesus
\r (Mark 3:31-35; Mat. 12:46-50)
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ45283 Yeshua's motherВҰ45287 andВҰ45283 brothersВҰ45291 arrivedВҰ45282 but they couldn't get close to him becauseВҰ45298 of the crowdВҰ45300.
\v 20 вҖңYourВҰ45309 motherВҰ45308 and brothersВҰ45312 are standing outsideВҰ45316,вҖқ someone told himВҰ45304, вҖңand they want to seeВҰ45317 you.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj MyВҰ45332 motherВҰ45331 and myВҰ45332 brothersВҰ45335,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ45325, вҖң\wj are anyone who's listening to God's messageВҰ45341 and who put it into practice.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's power over the wind and waves
\rem /s1 Jesus Calms a Storm; Jesus Calms the Storm
\r (Mark 4:35-41; Mat. 8:23-27)
\p
\v 22 One day Yeshua and hisВҰ45367 apprenticesВҰ45366 got into a boatВҰ45363 and he asked them to go acrossВҰ45375 to the other side of Lake \add Galilee\add*. SoВҰ45350 they set off
\v 23 butВҰ45381 once they were moving, Yeshua fell asleepВҰ45383. ThenВҰ45384 a big stormВҰ45386 descended onto the lake and the boat was beingВҰ45394 swampedВҰ45394 \add by the waves\add* and they were in dangerВҰ45396 \add of sinking\add*.
\v 24 The apprentices went and woke Yeshua, вҖңMasterВҰ45403, we're going to drown!вҖқ
\p Now awake, he spoke sternly to the windВҰ45413 and the waves in the lake, and they stopped and it becameВҰ45424 calm.
\v 25 вҖң\wj Where'sВҰ45429 yourВҰ45433 faithВҰ45432?\wj*вҖқ he asked them.
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Man with Demons; Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Man; Jesus Heals the Gerasene Demoniac; The Healing of a Demon-possessed Man
\rem /r (Matthew 8.28-34; Mark 5.1-20)
\p From being terrified, they were now astounded and asked each other, вҖңWho is this guy \add really\add*? He can just tell the wind and the waterВҰ45453 what to do, and they obeyВҰ45455 him!вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua drives many demons into the pigs
\r (Mark 5:1-20; Mat. 8:28-34)
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ45457 theyВҰ45458 sailedВҰ45458 across to the regionВҰ45463 of the GerasenesВҰ45466, whichВҰ45468 is across the lake from GalileeВҰ45472.
\v 27 As they got \add out of the boat\add*, a demon-possessed manВҰ45485 who'd comeВҰ45474 out of the cityВҰ45489 met him there. He didn'tВҰ45504 live in a houseВҰ45511, but lived in a cemetery, andВҰ45476 he wasn't wearing a lot.
\v 28 He yelledВҰ45525 out when he saw Yeshua and knelt down beforeВҰ45527 him, and spoke loudlyВҰ45531, вҖңWhat \add business\add* do you and I have together, Yeshua, son of the highestВҰ45543 \nd GodВҰ45541\nd*? I beg you, don'tВҰ45546 torture me.вҖқ
\v 29 \add He said this\add* becauseВҰ45552 Yeshua had commandedВҰ45550 the evil spiritВҰ45555 to comeВҰ45559 out from the manВҰ45564. The demon had animated him many timesВҰ45567 and he'd \add needed\add* to be put in chainsВҰ45573 and shacklesВҰ45575, but he would break them off and the demon would driveВҰ45584 him into the wildernessВҰ45594.
\p
\v 30 вҖң\wj What'sВҰ45602 your nameВҰ45605?\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* askedВҰ45596.
\p вҖңThousands,вҖқ he answered, becauseВҰ45614 many thousandsВҰ45611 of demonsВҰ45616 had entered him
\v 31 andВҰ45625 \add now\add* theyВҰ45627 were pleading with \add @Yeshua\add* not to commandВҰ45632 them to goВҰ45638 back to the bottomless pit.
\p
\v 32 \add They could see\add* a herd of pigs beingВҰ45646 fed on a hill, and they requested Yeshua to let them go into the pigs, and he agreed to that.
\v 33 SoВҰ45675 the demonsВҰ45677 rushed out of the manВҰ45680 and into the pigs, and all the pigs thenВҰ45675 rushed down the steepВҰ45694 bank into the lake and drownedВҰ45700.
\p
\v 34 When the \add workers\add* feedingВҰ45705 the pigs saw this happen, they took off and told everyone in the \add nearby\add* town and round about.
\v 35 \nd SoВҰ45723\nd* lots of people wentВҰ45722 \add there to the edge of the lake\add* to seeВҰ45727 for themselves, and they foundВҰ45736 the manВҰ45741 who'd been demon-possessed now dressed and sittingВҰ45738 at \nd Yeshua's\nd* feetВҰ45758 with his full faculties, and they were frightened.
\v 36 The people who'd seenВҰ45771 itВҰ45771 happen told the new-comers how the demon-possessed man had been healedВҰ45773.
\v 37 ThenВҰ45777 all those peopleВҰ45788 from the GerasenesВҰ45796 regionВҰ45792 askedВҰ45778 Yeshua to leave the area, becauseВҰ45801 they were \add quite\add* terrified, so he got back into the boatВҰ45812 andВҰ45777 \add they\add* headed back to the other side.
\p
\v 38 The manВҰ45822 who the demonsВҰ45827 had comeВҰ45825 out of had asked Yeshua if he could go with him, butВҰ45818 Yeshua sentВҰ45832 him away, sayingВҰ45838,
\v 39 вҖң\wj Go back to yourВҰ45844 houseВҰ45843 andВҰ45860 tell \+add them there\+add* about what \+nd GodВҰ45854\+nd* has done for you.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 A Girl Restored to Life and a Woman Healed; A Dead Girl and a Sick Woman; Jesus Heals in Response to Faith; Jairus' Daughter and the Woman Who Touched Jesus' Cloak
\rem /r (Matthew 9.18-26; Mark 5.21-43)
\p SoВҰ45860 he wentВҰ45861 around the town telling everyone what \nd Yeshua\nd* had done for him.
\s1 The leader's dying daughter plus the woman haemorrhaging
\r (Mark 5:21-43; Mat. 9:18-26)
\p
\v 40 When \nd Yeshua\nd* got back \add to the other side of the lake\add*, the crowdВҰ45888 \add there\add* had been waitingВҰ45893 for him andВҰ45876 welcomedВҰ45883 him.
\v 41 ThenВҰ45897, wowВҰ45898, a manВҰ45901 named YairusВҰ45907 cameВҰ45899 and knelt down in front of Yeshua. He was the leader at the \add local\add* meetingВҰ45913 hallВҰ45913 and he pleaded for Yeshua to comeВҰ45926 to hisВҰ45933 houseВҰ45931
\v 42 becauseВҰ45936 his only daughterВҰ45937, a twelve-year old, was dyingВҰ45947.
\p Then while Yeshua was on his way squeezing through the crowdВҰ45958,
\v 43 a womanВҰ45963 who'd had internal bleeding for twelveВҰ45970 yearsВҰ45969 andВҰ45962 who couldn't be helped \add by any doctor\add*,
\v 44 \add worked her way up\add* behindВҰ45996 Yeshua and touchedВҰ45997 the edge of hisВҰ46002 robe. Immediately her bleeding stoppedВҰ46005
\v 45 and \nd Yeshua\nd* \add stopped and\add* said, вҖң\wj Who touchedВҰ46025 me?\wj*вҖқ
\p No one owned up, and PeterВҰ46033 said, вҖңMasterВҰ46040, there's people all around you and they're pressing againstВҰ46026 you.вҖқ
\p
\v 46 вҖң\wj SomeoneВҰ46061 touchedВҰ46059 me,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ46058, вҖң\wj becauseВҰ46063 I felt powerВҰ46066 going out from me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 47 When the womanВҰ46074 now saw that she wouldn't get away with it, she cameВҰ46081 to Yeshua shaking, and knelt down at his feet. She told him in front of all the peopleВҰ46097 why she'd touchedВҰ46088 his \add clothes\add* and how she'd been immediatelyВҰ46103 healedВҰ46102.
\v 48 вҖң\wj \+add вүҲLady\+add*,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua saidВҰ46107, вҖң\wj yourВҰ46113 faithВҰ46112 has healedВҰ46114 you. Go in peaceВҰ46119.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 49 While he was still speakingВҰ46123, someoneВҰ46126 came from the meetingВҰ46130 hallВҰ46130 leader'sВҰ46130 \add home\add* and told \add him\add*, вҖңDon't bother the teacherВҰ46144 any further. YourВҰ46139 daughterВҰ46138 just passed away.вҖқ
\p
\v 50 But \nd Yeshua\nd* heardВҰ46148 this and \add turned to Yairus and\add* said, вҖң\wj Don't be afraid. Just believeВҰ46158 and she'll be healedВҰ46161.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 51 SoВҰ46164 they continued to the houseВҰ46167, but Yeshua didn'tВҰ46168 allowВҰ46170 anyoneВҰ46174 inside other than PeterВҰ46180 and Yohan and Yacob, along with the girl's parents.
\v 52 Everyone was weeping andВҰ46198 mourningВҰ46201 for her, butВҰ46204 he saidВҰ46205, вҖң\wj Don't cry. She isn'tВҰ46206 deadвҖ”just asleep.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 53 ButВҰ46214 they ridiculedВҰ46215 Yeshua because they knew that she'd diedВҰ46219.
\v 54 He took hold of herВҰ46230 handВҰ46229, andВҰ46221 calledВҰ46232, вҖң\wj Girl, get up.\wj*вҖқ
\v 55 ThenВҰ46238 her spiritВҰ46242 returnedВҰ46240 and she got up immediatelyВҰ46246, and he told \add <them\add* to give her somethingВҰ46251 to eatВҰ46253.
\v 56 HerВҰ46259 parentsВҰ46258 were astonished, but he instructedВҰ46264 them not to tell anyoneВҰ46268 what had happened.
\c 9
\s1 Yeshua sends out his twelve apprentices
\rem /s1 Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Disciples; Jesus and the Twelve; Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Apostles; The Mission of the Twelve
\r (Mark 6:7-13; Mat. 10:5-15)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ46273 Yeshua calledВҰ46272 togetherВҰ46272 his twelveВҰ46275 apprentices and gaveВҰ46279 them powerВҰ46282 and authorityВҰ46286 over all the demonsВҰ46291 and to heal diseasesВҰ46294,
\v 2 and then sentВҰ46297 them out to preach about God's kingdomВҰ46301 and to heal those who were sickВҰ46309.
\v 3 вҖң\wj Don't take anything for the journeyВҰ46319,\wj*вҖқ he told them. вҖң\wj Don't take a walking stick or a backpack or food or money or spare clothes.\wj*
\v 4 \wj When someone invites you into their home, stay in that one houseВҰ46340 until you leave that place,\wj*
\v 5 \x + \xo 9:5: \xt Acts 13:51.\x*\wj but when the people don'tВҰ46353 \+add вүҲwant to hear from\+add* you, shake the dust off yourВҰ46370 feetВҰ46369 as a testimonyВҰ46374 to them \+add that God will punish them for not receivingВҰ46354 his messengers\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ46379 they headed off, preachingВҰ46387 the goodВҰ46387 messageВҰ46387 andВҰ46379 healingВҰ46389 the people as they walked from village to village.
\s1 Herod is confused by the news
\rem /s1 Herod's Confusion; Herod's Perplexity
\r (Mark 6:14-29; Mat. 14:1-12)
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 9:7-8: \xt Mrk 8:28; Mat 16:14; Luk 9:19.\x*HerodВҰ46394 the rulerВҰ46396 of the \add Galilean\add* quarterВҰ46396 heardВҰ46391 about everything that was going on andВҰ46403 was completely puzzled, becauseВҰ46406 some people saidВҰ46408 that Yohan the immerser had come back to life,
\v 8 while others said that EliyahВҰ46423 had been spotted, and others that one of the other ancientВҰ46433 prophetsВҰ46429 had come back to life.
\v 9 вҖңI beheadedВҰ46443 Yohan,вҖқ \add King\add* HerodВҰ46439 saidВҰ46436, вҖңso who is this man that I'm hearingВҰ46453 so much about?вҖқ SoВҰ46437 heВҰ46456 tried to find a way to seeВҰ46457 himВҰ46458.
\s1 Yeshua feeds 5,000 families
\rem /s1 Jesus Feeds Five Thousand; Jesus Feeds the Five Thousand; Feeding the Five Thousand
\r (Yhn 6:1-14; Mark 6:30-44; Mat. 14:13-21)
\p
\v 10 When the \add twelve\add* apprentices returnedВҰ46461 \add back to Yeshua\add*, they reported back to him everything they'd done. ThenВҰ46460 he took them to the town of BethsaidaВҰ46491 for some private time,
\v 11 butВҰ46493 the crowdsВҰ46494 saw where he went and followedВҰ46496 afterВҰ46497 them, so he welcomedВҰ46499 them and taught them about God's kingdomВҰ46508 as well as healing those who needed it.
\p
\v 12 As the dayВҰ46523 was coming to an end, the twelveВҰ46530 approachedВҰ46527 himВҰ46532 and saidВҰ46531, вҖңSend the crowdВҰ46536 away so that they can go into the nearby towns and countrysideВҰ46547 to find somewhere to stay and something to eat, becauseВҰ46552 this placeВҰ46556 is very isolated.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 But Yeshua told them, вҖң\wj You all giveВҰ46565 them somethingВҰ46565 to eatВҰ46568.\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңWe don'tВҰ46589 have anything more than just fiveВҰ46583 breadrolls and twoВҰ46587 fish, unless weВҰ46591 go and buy some food for all these peopleВҰ46597.вҖқ
\v 14 There were about 5,000 menВҰ46604 \add (not counting women andВҰ46608 children)\add*.
\p ThenВҰ46608 he told hisВҰ46612 apprenticesВҰ46611, вҖң\wj Sit them down in rows of about fiftyВҰ46618 each.\wj*вҖқ
\v 15 SoВҰ46619 they did that andВҰ46619 everyone sat down.
\v 16 ThenВҰ46628 Yeshua took the fiveВҰ46630 breadrolls and the twoВҰ46634 fish and looking up to the skyВҰ46639, he blessedВҰ46642 them and brokeВҰ46646 them \add into pieces\add* to give to the apprenticesВҰ46650 to distribute to the crowdВҰ46655.
\v 17 Everyone ateВҰ46658 until they were satisfiedВҰ46660, andВҰ46657 thenВҰ46657 twelveВҰ46674 basketsВҰ46672 of leftoverВҰ46667 pieces were collected up afterwards.
\s1 Peter's recognition of the messiah
\rem /s1 Peter's Confession of Christ; Peter's Declaration about Jesus
\r (Mark 8:27-29; Mat. 16:13-19)
\p
\v 18 Later when it was the timeВҰ46679 to pray and Yeshua and the \add twelve moved away from the crowd,\add* he askedВҰ46696 them, вҖң\wj Who do the crowdsВҰ46706 say that I am?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \x + \xo 9:19: \xt Mrk 6:14-15; Mat 14:1-2; Luk 9:7-8.\x*вҖң\add Some say\add* Yohan-the-immerser,вҖқ theyВҰ46709 answeredВҰ46711, вҖңwhile others say Eliyah, andВҰ46717 others say that some other ancientВҰ46728 prophetВҰ46722 came back to life.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \x + \xo 9:20: \xt Yhn 6:68-69.\x*вҖң\wj And so who do you \+add guys\+add* say I am?\wj*вҖқ he asked.
\rem /s1 Jesus Foretells His Death and Resurrection; Jesus Speaks about His Suffering and Death; Jesus Predicts His Death
\rem /r (Matthew 16.20-28; Mark 8.30вҖ”9.1)
\p вҖң\add You're\add* the \nd messiahВҰ46747\nd* \add вүҲfrom\add* \nd GodВҰ46750\nd*,вҖқ PeterВҰ46742 answeredВҰ46744.
\s1 Yeshua tells about his coming suffering and death
\r (Mark 8:30-31; Mat. 16:20-21)
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ46752 Yeshua warnedВҰ46753 themвҖ”instructing them not to tell this to anyoneВҰ46756 \add else\add*,
\v 22 saying, вҖң\wj Humanity's child \+add вүҲis destined\+add* to sufferВҰ46770 many things and to be rejectedВҰ46772 by the eldersВҰ46776 and the chiefВҰ46778 priestsВҰ46778 and the religiousВҰ46780 teachersВҰ46780, and then to be executed and to be brought back to life on the thirdВҰ46786 dayВҰ46787.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The cost of following Yeshua
\r (Mark 8:34вҖ“9:1; Mat. 16:24-28)
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 9:23: \xt Mat 10:38; Luk 14:27.\x*Yeshua said, вҖң\wj If anyoneВҰ46797 wants to become my follower, thenВҰ46793 that person needsВҰ46804 to renounceВҰ46804 their own desires and follow me, even in suffering and death,\wj*
\v 24 \x + \xo 9:24: \xt Yhn 12:25; Mat 10:39; Luk 17:33.\x*\wj becauseВҰ46817 anyone who wants to save their own life will lose it, but anyone who is prepared to lose their life on accountВҰ46835 of me, they'll be savingВҰ46838 their life.\wj*
\v 25 \wj How would it benefitВҰ46842 a personВҰ46844 if they gainedВҰ46846 \+add the wealth\+add* of the wholeВҰ46850 worldВҰ46849, but then ended up lost or destroyedВҰ46853?\wj*
\v 26 \wj BecauseВҰ46859 anyone who's ashamed of me and myВҰ46863 teachings, humanity's child will be ashamed of that person when he comes in hisВҰ46880 splendour and with the splendour of the fatherВҰ46883 and of God's messengersВҰ46888.\wj*
\v 27 \wj But I can certainly tell youВҰ46891 that some of those who are standing here won'tВҰ46904 die untilВҰ46908 theyВҰ46911 seeВҰ46911 God's kingdomВҰ46914.\wj*
\s1 Yeshua talks with Mosheh and Eliyah
\rem /s1 The Transfiguration
\r (Mark 9:2-8; Mat. 17:1-8)
\p
\v 28 It was aboutВҰ46930 eightВҰ46932 daysВҰ46931 later that Yeshua took PeterВҰ46936 and Yohan and Yacob, and climbed a hill to pray.
\v 29 While he was prayingВҰ46954, the appearanceВҰ46959 of his faceВҰ46962 changed andВҰ46950 his clothesВҰ46969 turned brilliant whiteВҰ46971.
\v 30 ThenВҰ46973, look, there were twoВҰ46976 menВҰ46975 talking with himВҰ46979вҖ”Mosheh andВҰ46986 Eliyah!
\v 31 Those two who'd been \add in heaven\add* were talking about the end of hisВҰ46997 time here whichВҰ46998 was about to be actioned in Yerushalem.
\v 32 PeterВҰ47008 and the others had been exhausted and fallen asleep, but when they woke up they sawВҰ47018 the radiance of Yeshua and the other twoВҰ47024 standing there with him,
\v 33 but when it was timeВҰ47032 for the two to leave, PeterВҰ47040 saidВҰ47038 to \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖңMasterВҰ47047, it's goodВҰ47048 that we're here. We could make threeВҰ47060 shelters: one for you, one for Mosheh, andВҰ47029 one for Eliyah.вҖқ (ButВҰ47029 he didn'tВҰ47072 really know what he was sayingВҰ47076.)
\p
\v 34 While he was still speaking, a cloud appeared and enveloped them and they were afraidВҰ47087 as they entered the fog.
\v 35 \x + \xo 9:35: \xt Isa 42:1; Mrk 1:11; Mat 3:17; 12:18; Luk 3:22.\x*ThenВҰ47098 a voiceВҰ47099 came out of the cloudВҰ47104 that said, вҖңThis is myВҰ47110 son, the one that has been chosenВҰ47113. Listen to himВҰ47118.вҖқ
\p
\v 36 By the timeВҰ47124 that the voiceВҰ47127 had spoken, they could only \add see\add* \nd Yeshua\nd* in front of them. \add After this event\add*, they keptВҰ47135 what had happened to themselves andВҰ47121 didn't tell anyoneВҰ47137 else about what they'd seenВҰ47146.
\s1 Yeshua heals a demon-possessed boy
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Boy with an Evil Spirit; Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Boy; The Healing of a Boy With an Evil Spirit; Jesus Heals a Boy with a Demon
\r (Mark 9:14-27; Mat. 17:14-18)
\p
\v 37 When they came back down the hill the next dayВҰ47155, a big crowdВҰ47167 was waiting for them.
\v 38 ThenВҰ47171, look, a manВҰ47173 in the crowdВҰ47176 shoutedВҰ47177 out, вҖңTeacherВҰ47180, I implore you to come andВҰ47171 look at my son, becauseВҰ47189 he's my only child.
\v 39 A spiritВҰ47196 takes control of him and suddenlyВҰ47201 he cries out and it makes him convulseВҰ47208 and foam at the mouth, and only leaves him after a long time when he's bruisedВҰ47219 \add and battered\add*.
\v 40 I tried to get yourВҰ47226 apprenticesВҰ47225 to drive itВҰ47231 out, but they couldn't.вҖқ
\p
\v 41 вҖң\wj Oh you unbelievingВҰ47243 and pervertedВҰ47245 generationВҰ47242,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ47236, вҖң\wj how much longer do I have to be with you and put up with all of you? BringВҰ47258 yourВҰ47256 son here.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 42 While they were stillВҰ47264 approachingВҰ47267, the demonВҰ47272 attackedВҰ47269 the boy and threwВҰ47275 him in a convulsionВҰ47275, butВҰ47277 \nd Yeshua\nd* rebukedВҰ47276 the evil spiritВҰ47281 and healedВҰ47286 the boy and led him back to hisВҰ47268 fatherВҰ47297.
\v 43 Everyone there was astounded at God's power.
\s1 Yeshua talks again about his death
\rem /s1 Jesus Again Foretells His Death; Jesus Again Predicts His Death; Jesus Speaks Again about His Death
\r (Mark 9:30-32; Mat. 17:22-23)
\p While all the people were still amazedВҰ47299 at what he'd done, Yeshua \add turned andВҰ47301\add* saidВҰ47319 to hisВҰ47323 apprenticesВҰ47322,
\v 44 вҖң\wj Remember everything that's been said, becauseВҰ47334 humanity's child is goingВҰ47338 to be turned in and placed into the handsВҰ47341 of \+add theseВҰ47332\+add* peopleВҰ47342.\wj*вҖқ
\v 45 But \add the apprentices\add* didn'tВҰ47345 know what he meant as it was hidden from them so they couldn't comprehend it, plus they were afraid to askВҰ47362 him to explain further.
\s1 Who is the greatest?
\rem /s1 True Greatness; Who Will Be the Greatest; The Greatest in the Kingdom; Who Is the Greatest?
\r (Mark 9:33-37; Mat. 18:1-5)
\p
\v 46 \x + \xo 9:46: \xt Luk 22:24.\x*ThenВҰ47369 the apprentices got themselves into a discussion about which of them \add вүҲmightВҰ47376\add* hopefully \add вүҲbe considered\add* the greatestВҰ47377.
\v 47 But \nd Yeshua\nd* knew what was going on, so he took a young child and stoodВҰ47394 the child there next to him
\v 48 \x + \xo 9:48: \xt Yhn 13:20; Mat 10:40; Luk 10:16.\x*and told them, вҖң\wj Anyone who accepts a young childВҰ47408 in myВҰ47413 nameВҰ47412 is accepting me, and anyone who accepts me is accepted by the one who sentВҰ47427 me here. BecauseВҰ47430 it's the person who is the leastВҰ47431 amongВҰ47432 youВҰ47434 who's \+add вүҲat the top\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Anyone who's not against you is for you
\rem /s1 Whoever Is Not against You Is for You; Using the Name of Jesus; Another Exorcist
\r (Mark 9:38-40)
\p
\v 49 вҖңMasterВҰ47448,вҖқ YohanВҰ47445 answeredВҰ47442, вҖңwe sawВҰ47449 someoneВҰ47450 drivingВҰ47456 out demonsВҰ47458 using yourВҰ47455 nameВҰ47454, andВҰ47443 we told himВҰ47462 to stop becauseВҰ47463 he's not one of us.вҖқ
\p
\v 50 вҖң\wj Don't forbidВҰ47476 \+add people like\+add* him,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* replied, вҖң\wj becauseВҰ47480 anyone who's not againstВҰ47483 you all, is \+add вүҲon your side\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua gets snubbed by a village in Shomron/Samaria
\rem /s1 Samaritan Opposition; The journey to Jerusalem; Opposition from Samaritans; A Samaritan Village Refuses to Receive Jesus
\p
\v 51 It was now coming to the timeВҰ47494 when the events leading to his ascensionВҰ47500 would start happening, andВҰ47502 Yeshua was \add вүҲcompletely set in his decision\add* to head to Yerushalem.
\p
\v 52 He sentВҰ47516 \add some of his\add* \add вүҲapprentices\add* ahead of him, andВҰ47523 \add when\add* they arrived at a SamaritanВҰ47530 villageВҰ47529, they wentВҰ47525 to get ready for his arrival.
\v 53 However, the people there didn'tВҰ47536 welcome them becauseВҰ47540 \add it was clear that\add* Yeshua \add вүҲwas heading\add* to Yerushalem.
\v 54 \x + \xo 9:54: \xt 2Ki 1:9-16.\x*Seeing this, his apprenticesВҰ47553 Yacob andВҰ47551 Yohan asked, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ47559\nd*, will youВҰ47560 let us call fireВҰ47562 down from the skyВҰ47567 to burn them up?вҖқ
\p
\v 55 However, Yeshua turnedВҰ47575 around and told them off,
\v 56 \add вүҲso\add* theyВҰ47601 headed off to anotherВҰ47603 villageВҰ47604.
\s1 Those who would have liked to follow Yeshua
\rem /s1 The Cost of Following Jesus; The Would-Be Followers of Jesus
\r (Mat. 8:19-22)
\p
\v 57 As they headed down the roadВҰ47612, someoneВҰ47620 told Yeshua, вҖңI'll followВҰ47623 you whereverВҰ47625 you go to.вҖқ
\p
\v 58 вҖң\wj \+nd FoxesВҰ47636\+nd* have their burrowsВҰ47639,\wj*вҖқ he respondedВҰ47633, вҖң\wj and the birdsВҰ47643 have their nestsВҰ47646, but humanity's child has no \+add home\+add* where he can lie down \+add and relax\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 59 Later he told a different person, вҖң\wj Follow me.\wj*вҖқ
\p ButВҰ47660 the man replied, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ47668\nd*, just let me go andВҰ47660 buryВҰ47676 myВҰ47679 fatherВҰ47678 firstВҰ47673.вҖқ
\p
\v 60 вҖң\wj LeaveВҰ47687 those who are dead to buryВҰ47690 the dead by themselvesВҰ47692,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua saidВҰ47680, вҖң\wj butВҰ47682 you go and tell \+add people\+add* about God's kingdomВҰ47701.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 61 \x + \xo 9:61: \xt 1Ki 19:20.\x*Also, anotherВҰ47707 person saidВҰ47704, вҖңI'll followВҰ47708 afterВҰ47709 youВҰ47709, \nd masterВҰ47710\nd*, butВҰ47713 firstВҰ47711 let me go back andВҰ47705 say goodbyeВҰ47717 to everyone at homeВҰ47721.вҖқ
\p
\v 62 But \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ47723, вҖң\wj No one who starts ploughing a field and then starts lookingВҰ47749 backwards is suitableВҰ47753 for God's kingdomВҰ47759.\wj*вҖқ
\c 10
\s1 Yeshua sends out 72 people
\rem /s1 Jesus Sends Out the Seventy-two; Jesus Sends Out His Disciples; The Mission of the Seventy
\p
\v 1 After all this, the \nd masterВҰ47770\nd* appointedВҰ47768 seventy-two othersВҰ47772 and he sentВҰ47776 them out in pairs to go ahead of him to everyВҰ47785 town and village that he would pass through.
\v 2 \x + \xo 10:2: \xt Mat 9:37-38.\x*He told them, вҖң\wj There'sВҰ47811 a large harvest \+add ready\+add*, but there's only a few workers. SoВҰ47811 ask the owner of the crop to send out more workers to help with hisВҰ47826 harvest.\wj*
\v 3 \x + \xo 10:3: \xt Mat 10:16.\x*\wj So get movingвҖ”seeВҰ47828, I'm sendingВҰ47830 youВҰ47831 out like lambsВҰ47834 with wolvesВҰ47838 all around.\wj*
\v 4 \wj Don't take a walletВҰ47841 or backpack or \+add spare\+add* sandalsВҰ47846, andВҰ47847 don't greetВҰ47852 people on the roadВҰ47851.\wj*
\p
\v 5 вҖң\wj Whenever you're welcomed into a home, firstВҰ47863 say, вҖҳPeaceВҰ47866 to this house.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 6 \wj And if there's someone there worthy of peace\f + \fr 10:6 \ft It's not obvious what Yeshua is referring to here with вҖҳson of peaceвҖҷ.\f*, thenВҰ47871 your peace will rest on that home, but if not, your peace will returnВҰ47892 to you.\wj*
\v 7 \x + \xo 10:7: \xt 1Cor 9:14; 1Tim 5:18.\x*\wj ThenВҰ47899 stay in that same house and eat and drinkВҰ47907 what they give you, becauseВҰ47912 the workerВҰ47914 is worthyВҰ47911 of hisВҰ47917 compensation. Don't be movingВҰ47920 from house to house.\wj*
\v 8 \wj Whenever you all go into some place andВҰ47926 the locals accept you, thenВҰ47926 eat what they give you.\wj*
\v 9 \wj Heal the sickВҰ47949 there andВҰ47951 tell them that God's kingdomВҰ47958 is near.\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 10:10-11: \xt Acts 13:51.\x*\wj But if you all go into some place and they don'tВҰ47970 accept you, then go out to the roadsВҰ47977 and announce,\wj*
\v 11 \x + \xo 10:4-11: \xt Mrk 6:8-11; Mat 10:7-14; Luk 9:3-5.\x*\wj вҖҳWe're wipingВҰ47996 off even the dust from yourВҰ47991 place that stuck to our footwear, howeverВҰ47998 you all need to know \+add anyway\+add* that God's kingdomВҰ48010 is near.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 10:12: a \xt Gen 19:24-28; Mat 11:24; \xo b \xt Mat 10:15.\x*\wj I'm telling youВҰ48015 that it will be more bearable for the people of SodomВҰ48017 in that dayВҰ48025 than for the people in that place.\wj*
\s1 Those who ignore the good message
\rem /s1 The Unbelieving Towns; Woes to Unrepentant Cities
\r (Mat. 11:20-24)
\p
\v 13 \x + \xo 10:13: \xt Isa 23:1-18; Eze 26:1вҖ“28:26; Yoel 3:4-8; Amos 1:9-10; Zech 9:2-4.\x*вҖң\wj You won't end well, Korazin. And you won't end well, BethsaidaВҰ48041. BecauseВҰ48042 if the miraclesВҰ48052 thatВҰ48053 were done in your places had been done in TyreВҰ48045 and Tsidon, they wouldВҰ48058 have turned around from disobeying God and shown their humility longВҰ48057 ago\wj*
\v 14 \wj hence it will be more tolerableВҰ48071 for TyreВҰ48068 and TsidonВҰ48070 on judgementВҰ48075 \+add day\+add* than it will be for you all.\wj*
\v 15 \x + \xo 10:15: \xt Isa 14:13-15.\x*\wj And you, CapernaumВҰ48081, don'tВҰ48082 think you'll be heading up to heavenВҰ48086, because it'll be down to hell for you.\wj*
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 10:16: \xt Yhn 13:20; Mrk 9:37; Mat 10:40; Luk 9:48.\x*вҖң\wj Anyone who listens to all of you, will be hearing from me, and anyone who rejects you all will be rejecting me, and anyone who rejects me is rejecting the one who sent me here.\wj*
\s1 The return of the 72
\rem /s1 The Return of the Seventy-Two
\p
\v 17 \add In time,\add* the seventy-two \add that had been sent out\add* came back excited, sayingВҰ48134, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ48135\nd*, even the demonsВҰ48138 listened to us when we used yourВҰ48145 nameВҰ48144 \add andВҰ48126 authority\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖң\wj I saw SatanВҰ48151,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua replied, вҖң\wj when he fell out of heavenВҰ48157 like lightningВҰ48153.\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 10:19: \xt Psa 91:13.\x*\wj ListenВҰ48161, I've givenВҰ48163 you all the authorityВҰ48166 to treadВҰ48168 on snakes and scorpionsВҰ48174 and to overcome the enemy'sВҰ48182 powerВҰ48179, and nothingВҰ48184 at all will be able to injureВҰ48188 you.\wj*
\v 20 \wj HoweverВҰ48190, don'tВҰ48193 get excited that the \+add evil\+add* spiritsВҰ48198 obeyed you, but rather be happy that yourВҰ48207 namesВҰ48206 have been written down in the heavensВҰ48213.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's happiness
\rem /s1 Jesus Rejoices; Jesus' Prayer of Thanksgiving
\r (Mat. 11:25-27; 13:16-17)
\p
\v 21 At the same time, the holy \nd spiritВҰ48224\nd* got Yeshua excited and he said, вҖң\wj I'm aware father, \+nd masterВҰ48235\+nd* of heavenВҰ48237 and earthВҰ48240, that you've hiddenВҰ48242 theseВҰ48243 things away from those who are intelligentВҰ48248 and well-educated, and \+add instead\+add* revealedВҰ48251 them to infantsВҰ48253. Yes, father, that was what you decided.\wj*
\p
\v 22 \x + \xo 10:22: a \xt Yhn 3:35; \xo b \xt Yhn 10:15.\x*\wj Everything has been handed over to me by myВҰ48278 father, and no one knows who the son is except for the father, and who the father is except for the son and those who the son decides to revealВҰ48308 him to.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ48309 he turnedВҰ48310 to his apprenticesВҰ48314 andВҰ48309 saidВҰ48317 discreetly, вҖң\wj BlessedВҰ48319 are those who get to see what you all are seeing\wj*
\v 24 \wj becauseВҰ48331 I can tell you that many prophetsВҰ48335 and kingsВҰ48337 wantedВҰ48338 to see what you all are seeingВҰ48342, but they didn'tВҰ48344 get to see what you've seen, nor to hearВҰ48347 what you all have heardВҰ48354.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 How to be a neighbour
\rem /s1 The Most Important Commandment; The Parable of the Good Samaritan
\p
\v 25 \x + \xo 10:25-28: \xt Mrk 12:28-34; Mat 22:35-40.\x*ThenВҰ48356 look, a lawyerВҰ48360 stoodВҰ48362 up to test himВҰ48364, asking, вҖңTeacherВҰ48367, what do I need to do to inheritВҰ48373 eternalВҰ48372 lifeВҰ48371?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj \+add Well,\+add* what's writtenВҰ48385 in the scriptures?\wj*вҖқ respondedВҰ48376 Yeshua. вҖң\wj How do youВҰ48387 understand them?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \x + \xo 10:27: a \xt Deu 6:5; \xo b \xt Lev 19:18.\x*вҖңYou must love your \nd GodВҰ48395 YahwehВҰ48393\nd* with all your heartВҰ48403 and all your soulВҰ48414, and all your strengthВҰ48424 and all your mindВҰ48403,вҖқ he replied. вҖңAlso, \add you must love\add* your neighbourВҰ48438 as yourselfВҰ48442.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 \x + \xo 10:28: \xt Lev 18:5.\x*вҖң\wj You've answered correctlyВҰ48446,\wj*вҖқ answered Yeshua, вҖң\wj so do that andВҰ48444 you'll live \+add forever\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 29 ButВҰ48465 \add the lawyer\add* wanted to justifyВҰ48457 his \add lifestyle\add*, so he asked, вҖң\nd AndВҰ48464\nd* who's myВҰ48468 neighbourВҰ48469?вҖқ
\rem /s1 Story of the Good Samaritan
\p
\v 30 \nd Yeshua\nd* repliedВҰ48470 \add with this\add*: вҖң\wj Once a \add Jewish\add* manВҰ48476 was walking downhill from Yerushalem to YerichoВҰ48484 when \+add a group of\+add* robbersВҰ48487 grabbed him and took \+add everything including\+add* his clothes, then took off leaving him there woundedВҰ48495 and half-dead.\wj*
\v 31 \wj ThenВҰ48506 it so happened that a priestВҰ48507 came down that same road, but when he saw him he continued past on the other side of the road.\wj*
\v 32 \wj Similarly, a priestly worker (a Levite) arrived at that placeВҰ48526 andВҰ48520 when he saw him he too passedВҰ48531 by on the other side.\wj*
\v 33 \x + \xo 10:33-34: \xt 2Ch 28:15.\x*\wj Then a man from ShomronВҰ48532 \add (SamariaВҰ48532)\add*\f + \fr 10:33 \ft The Judeans and the Samaritans despised each other and disagreed on many vital issues.\f* who was on a trip cameВҰ48536 across him, and when he saw him he felt sorry for him\wj*
\v 34 \wj and went up to him and bandaged his woundsВҰ48547, pouringВҰ48549 oliveВҰ48551 oil and wine on them, then put him on his own animal and took him to a roadhouse and looked after him.\wj*
\v 35 \wj The next dayВҰ48572 he took out twoВҰ48579 coinsВҰ48580 and gaveВҰ48578 them to their host, instructing, вҖҳLook after this guy and if it costs more than this, I'll reimburse you on my wayВҰ48599 back.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 36 вҖң\wj So which of those threeВҰ48610 do youВҰ48614 think acted like the neighbourВҰ48611 of the one attacked by robbersВҰ48621?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 37 вҖңThe one who cared for him,вҖқ replied \add the lawyer\add*.
\rem /s1 At the Home of Martha and Mary; Jesus Visits Martha and Mary
\p вҖң\wj ThenВҰ48623 you go andВҰ48623 do the same,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* told him.
\s1 Yeshua visits Martha and Maria
\p
\v 38 \x + \xo 10:38-39: \xt Yhn 11:1.\x*When it was timeВҰ48648 to leave, Yeshua wentВҰ48654 into a villageВҰ48658 andВҰ48661 there was a womanВҰ48660 there named MarthaВҰ48664 who welcomedВҰ48665 himВҰ48666 in.
\v 39 She had a sisterВҰ48678 named MariaВҰ48680 who was also sitting there \add on the floor\add* by \nd Yeshua's\nd* feetВҰ48688 listening to hisВҰ48697 teaching.
\v 40 But MarthaВҰ48700 kept getting pulledВҰ48701 away to keep the household running, and \add after a while\add* approachedВҰ48705 Yeshua and asked, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ48710\nd*, doesn't itВҰ48713 bother youВҰ48714 that myВҰ48718 sisterВҰ48717 has left all the housework to me? Tell herВҰ48729 to come and helpВҰ48735 me.вҖқ
\p
\v 41 вҖң\wj Martha, Martha,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answeredВҰ48736, вҖң\wj you are worried and concerned aboutВҰ48752 many things,\wj*
\v 42 \wj butВҰ48756 only one thing really matters. MariaВҰ48762 choseВҰ48769 the best thing, and it won'tВҰ48772 be takenВҰ48773 away from herВҰ48775.\wj*вҖқ
\c 11
\s1 Yeshua teaches about prayer
\rem /s1 Jesus' Teaching on Prayer; The Lord's Prayer
\r (Mat. 6:9-13; 7:7-11)
\p
\v 1 One time Yeshua was at a placeВҰ48784 praying, andВҰ48776 when he finished some of his followers asked him, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ48797\nd*, Yohan-the-immerser taughtВҰ48804 his apprentices how to pray. You teachВҰ48798 us as well.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 SoВҰ48810 Yeshua told them, вҖң\wj WheneverВҰ48813 you all pray, say this:\wj*
\q1 \wj Father, may \+add вүҲall people honour you as their holy God\+add*.\wj*
\q1 \wj May \+add вүҲyou reign as king\+add* \+add over the earth\+add*.\wj*
\q1
\v 3 \wj Every dayВҰ48872 give us the food thatВҰ48870 we need.\wj*
\q1
\v 4 \wj Forgive us for ourВҰ48881 sinsВҰ48879 becauseВҰ48884 we've forgivenВҰ48875 those who owed \+add something\+add* to us.\wj*
\q1 \wj Don't bring us into \+add situations where\+add* we're temptedВҰ48900.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Perseverance in Prayer
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ48907 heВҰ48908 told them, вҖң\wj \+add Imagine\+add* youВҰ48913 had a friendВҰ48915 and went to them at midnightВҰ48920 and asked, вҖҳFriendВҰ48927, lend me some bread\wj*
\v 6 \wj because a travelling friendВҰ48933 of mine arrivedВҰ48936 at myВҰ48934 place, andВҰ48944 I haven't got anything to give himВҰ48949 to eat.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 7 \wj And the one in the \+add other\+add* house might reply, вҖҳDon't bother me \+add now\+add* because the house is locked and the kids are asleep beside me here in the bed. I can'tВҰ48958 get up and get anythingВҰ48989 for youВҰ48990.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 8 \wj I'm telling all of you that even if that friend wouldn't get up and give them anything because of their friendship, then the friend will certainly get up and give them \+add some food\+add* if they persistВҰ49011 \+add in knocking\+add*.\wj*
\v 9 \wj SoВҰ49021 this is what I'm telling you: \+add Keep submitting\+add* your requestsВҰ49026 and it'll be givenВҰ49028 to you all, keep searching and you'll all find \+add what you're lookingВҰ49030 for\+add*, keep knockingВҰ49033 and the door will be openedВҰ49035 for you all,\wj*
\v 10 \wj becauseВҰ49038 everyone who requestsВҰ49040 will receiveВҰ49041, and everyone who searches will find, and everyone who knocksВҰ49048 will find openedВҰ49049 \+add doors\+add*.\wj*
\v 11 \wj How many of you fathersВҰ49059, if yourВҰ49056 child asked you for \+add some\+add* fish, you'd give them a snake insteadВҰ49078?\wj*
\v 12 \wj Or the child would ask for an egg and you'd pass them a scorpionВҰ49100?\wj*
\v 13 \wj SoВҰ49112 if you all know how to give goodВҰ49119 things to your childrenВҰ49123 despite your beingВҰ49116 evilВҰ49114, how much more the fatherВҰ49128 in heavenВҰ49132 will give the holy \+nd spiritВҰ49135\+nd* to those who ask himВҰ49141.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is accused of being demon-possessed
\rem /s1 Opposition and questioning; Jesus and the Prince of Demons; Jesus and Beelzebul; Jesus and Beelzebub
\r (Mark 3:20-27; Mat. 12:22-30)
\p
\v 14 ThenВҰ49149 Yeshua drove out a demon that caused muteness, andВҰ49149 after the demon departed, the manВҰ49169 was able to speak. The crowdsВҰ49175 were amazed,
\v 15 \x + \xo 11:15: \xt Mat 9:34; 10:25.\x*butВҰ49178 yet some of them saidВҰ49183, вҖңHe's drivingВҰ49192 out demons because he's Beelzebul the leader of the demons.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 11:16: \xt Mrk 8:11; Mat 12:38; 16:1.\x*Others who wanted to test \add who he was\add*, asked Yeshua to send a signВҰ49209 from heaven,
\v 17 butВҰ49220 he knew theirВҰ49222 thoughtsВҰ49224 and told them, вҖң\wj Any kingdomВҰ49229 that's divided against itselfВҰ49233 is doomed, and any household that's divided will self-destruct.\wj*
\v 18 \wj SoВҰ49244 if SatanВҰ49247 was fighting againstВҰ49248 himselfВҰ49249, how could hisВҰ49258 kingdomВҰ49257 even remain? Yes, I know that you're all sayingВҰ49261 that I must be Beelzebul in order to drive out demonsВҰ49270,\wj*
\v 19 \wj but if I have Beelzebul's power over demons, thenВҰ49272 whose power do \+em yourВҰ49281\+em* apprentices use to drive out demons?\wj*
\v 20 \wj However if I'm drivingВҰ49306 out demonsВҰ49308 with power that comes from God, then that means that God's kingdomВҰ49314 is right in the middle of youВҰ49312 all.\wj*
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj WheneverВҰ49317 a strongВҰ49319 \+add landowner\+add* arms himselfВҰ49325 and guardsВҰ49322 hisВҰ49334 nice home, everything remains there peacefullyВҰ49329,\wj*
\v 22 \wj but when someone strongerВҰ49339 than him arrives and overpowers him, he'll even take the body armour thatВҰ49353 the \+add landowner\+add* put his trustВҰ49354 in, and then relieve him of all his goods.\wj*
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 11:23: \xt Mrk 9:40.\x*вҖң\wj Anyone who doesn't \+add follow\+add* me is againstВҰ49368 me, andВҰ49371 anyone who doesn't gatherВҰ49374 with us, \+add wants to\+add* scatterВҰ49377 us.\wj*
\s1 The return of demons
\rem /s1 The Return of the Evil Spirit; The Return of the Unclean Spirit
\r (Mat. 12:43-45)
\p
\v 24 вҖң\wj Whenever an evil spiritВҰ49383 leaves a personВҰ49387, it roams through inhospitable placesВҰ49393 lookingВҰ49394 forВҰ49394 \+add somewhere to\+add* rest, and when it doesn't find \+add a home\+add*, it says, вҖҳ\+add Ah,\+add* I'll returnВҰ49403 to the home that I recently leftВҰ49409.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 25 \wj ThenВҰ49410 when it gets back there, it finds the home sweptВҰ49415 out andВҰ49410 tidied up,\wj*
\v 26 \wj so itВҰ49419 goes and finds sevenВҰ49430 otherВҰ49426 spiritsВҰ49427 more evilВҰ49428 than itselfВҰ49429. They all move in and live thereВҰ49435, so the result is that the personВҰ49441 ends up worseВҰ49443 in the end than \+add they were\+add* at the beginning.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 God's true reward
\rem /s1 True Blessedness; True Happiness
\p
\v 27 While Yeshua was teaching theseВҰ49452 things, a womanВҰ49459 in the crowdВҰ49462 shouted out, вҖңBlessedВҰ49465 is the mother who bore you andВҰ49447 the one who raised you.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 вҖң\wj Actually,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua replied, вҖң\wj the ones who will be blessedВҰ49482 are all those who listen to God's messageВҰ49486 andВҰ49489 put itВҰ49490 into practice.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The crowd requests a miracle
\rem /s1 The Demand for a Miracle; The Sign of Jonah
\r (Mat. 12:38-42)
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 11:29: \xt Mrk 8:12; Mat 16:4.\x*The crowdsВҰ49498 had grown even larger, but Yeshua told them, вҖң\wj This generation is evil because they're requesting a miracle andВҰ49497 the only miracle that will be givenВҰ49515 to them will be the miracle of YonahВҰ49521 \+add (Jonah)\+add*.\wj*
\v 30 \x + \xo 11:30: \xt Yonah 3:4.\x*\wj In the same way that Yonah becameВҰ49526 a signВҰ49532 to the \+add citizens\+add* of Ninevah, so too humanity's child will also be to this generationВҰ49541.\wj*
\v 31 \x + \xo 11:31: \xt 1Ki 10:1-10; 2Ch 9:1-12.\x*\wj The queenВҰ49566 from the southВҰ49567 will come back to life on judgementВҰ49571 \+add day\+add* along with the people from this generationВҰ49577, and she'll condemnВҰ49580 them, becauseВҰ49583 she travelled a long distance to hearВҰ49590 Solomon's wisdomВҰ49592, and now, someone's here who's greaterВҰ49596 than Solomon.\wj*
\v 32 \x + \xo 11:32: \xt Yonah 3:5.\x*\wj The people of Ninevah will standВҰ49602 up on judgementВҰ49605 \+add day\+add* along with the people from this generation and they'll condemnВҰ49611 this generation becauseВҰ49613 those from Ninevah turned from their disobedience after Yonah's preaching, and now, someone's here who's greaterВҰ49621 than Yonah.\wj*
\s1 The eye is the body's lamp
\rem /s1 Receiving the Light; The Lamp of the Body; The Light of the Body
\r (Mat. 5:15; 6:22-23)
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 11:33: \xt Mrk 4:21; Mat 5:15; Luk 8:16.\x*вҖң\wj No one lights a lamp and then hides it somewhere or puts it underВҰ49634 a basketВҰ49636, but rather they put it on a lampstandВҰ49640 so that everyoneВҰ49625 enteringВҰ49643 \+add the roomВҰ49630\+add* can see the lightВҰ49645 \+add from it\+add*.\wj*
\v 34 \wj YourВҰ49657 eyes are like the lamp for your body. WheneverВҰ49658 your eyes are healthyВҰ49664, your \+add entireВҰ49668\+add* body will be brightВҰ49672, but when your eyes are evil, your body is also dark,\wj*
\v 35 \wj so take care in case the lightВҰ49695 in youВҰ49698 has gone dark.\wj*
\v 36 \wj ThereforeВҰ49705 if yourВҰ49708 wholeВҰ49709 bodyВҰ49707 is bright without any dark areas, itВҰ49719 will be bright all over, like when a lamp shines on you to illuminateВҰ49729 you.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's warning about the religious teachers
\rem /s1 Jesus Denounces Pharisees and Lawyers; Jesus Accuses the Pharisees and the Teachers of the Law; Jesus Criticizes the Religious Leaders; Six Woes
\r (Mark 12:38-40; Mat. 23:1-36)
\p
\v 37 When Yeshua \add had a break from\add* speakingВҰ49734, a memberВҰ49743 of the Pharisee partyВҰ49743 invited him over for breakfast, so he went into the house andВҰ49732 satВҰ49755 down,
\v 38 andВҰ49757 the man was very surprised that he didn'tВҰ49769 observe the handwashing ceremony beforeВҰ49773 he ate.
\v 39 But the \nd masterВҰ49779\nd* saidВҰ49776 to his host, вҖң\wj Yes, all of you in the Pharisee partyВҰ49785 cleanВҰ49794 the outsideВҰ49788 of the cup and the plate, butВҰ49777 yourВҰ49799 insidesВҰ49798 are full of theftВҰ49802 and wickednessВҰ49804.\wj*
\v 40 \wj How stupid! Didn't \+add God\+add* who made the outsideВҰ49812 part, also make what's insideВҰ49816?\wj*
\v 41 \wj HoweverВҰ49818, if you sacrificially giveВҰ49821 what's inside, then everything would then become cleanВҰ49827 for you.\wj*
\p
\v 42 \x + \xo 11:42: \xt Lev 27:30.\x*вҖң\wj ButВҰ49860 you PhariseesВҰ49836 won'tВҰ49867 end well, becauseВҰ49838 you give a tenth of your herbs and vegetables, yet you all ignore giving justiceВҰ49853 and loving \+nd GodВҰ49858\+nd*, both of which need to be done and cannot be ignored.\wj*
\p
\v 43 вҖң\wj You Pharisees won't end well, becauseВҰ49877 you all love the best seats in the meetingВҰ49883 hallsВҰ49883 and the \+add honoured\+add* greetingsВҰ49886 in the marketplacesВҰ49890.\wj*
\v 44 \wj You all won'tВҰ49920 end well, becauseВҰ49904 you're like unmarked graves that people walkВҰ49916 all over without even realising\+add вҖ”the people simply don'tВҰ49920 know that you're dead inside\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 45 One of the experts in religious rules \add there\add* answeredВҰ49922 himВҰ49928 \add back\add*, вҖңTeacherВҰ49929, you'reВҰ49934 insultingВҰ49934 us as well when you say that.вҖқ
\p
\v 46 вҖң\wj \+add Well,\+add* you law experts won'tВҰ49960 end well,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ49937, вҖң\wj because you put unbearablyВҰ49952 \+add heavy\+add* burdens onto the shoulders of the peopleВҰ49948, yet you wouldn't move yourВҰ49959 \+add little\+add* fingersВҰ49958 to touchВҰ49961 those burdens yourselvesВҰ49954.\wj*
\v 47 \wj You all won't end well, becauseВҰ49966 you all buildВҰ49967 \+add fancy\+add* tombsВҰ49969 for the prophetsВҰ49971 that yourВҰ49976 own ancestorsВҰ49975 executed.\wj*
\v 48 \wj Because of that, you're all \+add actually\+add* admitting and agreeing to what yourВҰ49991 ancestorsВҰ49990 did, becauseВҰ49992 they killedВҰ49995 them and \+add then\+add* you buildВҰ49999 theirВҰ49999 tombsВҰ49999.\wj*
\v 49 \wj That's why \+nd GodВҰ50009\+nd* in his wisdomВҰ50007 saidВҰ50010, вҖҳI'll send prophetsВҰ50015 and missionaries to them, which they will \+add then\+add* persecuteВҰ50023 and kill\wj*вҖҷ
\v 50 \wj so thatВҰ50032 the bloodВҰ50028 of those prophetsВҰ50031 whichВҰ50032 was spilt from the creation of the worldВҰ50037 \+add onwards\+add* would then be charged to this generationВҰ50041.\wj*
\v 51 \x + \xo 11:51: a \xt Gen 4:8; \xo b \xt 2Ch 24:20-21.\x*\wj \+add This goes all the way back to\+add* to the blood of HevelВҰ50046 \add (Abel)\add*, right up to the blood of Zekaryah who was \+add recently\+add* killed betweenВҰ50059 the altarВҰ50061 and the temple sanctuary. Yes, I'm telling all of you, \+add those crimes\+add* will be charged to \+em this\+em* generationВҰ50073.\wj*
\p
\v 52 вҖң\wj You religious law experts won'tВҰ50089 end well, becauseВҰ50080 you tookВҰ50082 away the key to knowledgeВҰ50086вҖ”not only did you not enter \+add yourselvesВҰ50088\+add*, but you also forbadeВҰ50095 others from entering.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 53 Once Yeshua left that \add house\add*, the religiousВҰ50114 teachersВҰ50114 and the Pharisee partyВҰ50118 started strongly resentingВҰ50121 him, and started \add a plan of\add* asking him more questions
\v 54 in the hope of catchingВҰ50134 an answer \add that could be used to condemn him\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Everything hidden will be revealed
\rem /s1 A Warning against Hypocrisy; Warnings and Encouragements
\r (Mat. 10:26-27)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 12:1: \xt Mrk 8:15; Mat 16:6.\x*By then the crowdВҰ50160 had grown to many thousandsВҰ50158, so much so that they were tramplingВҰ50163 on each other. Meanwhile Yeshua told hisВҰ50172 followers, вҖң\wj \+add вүҲMake sure that you're not influenced by the hypocrisyВҰ50183 of the Pharisee partyВҰ50180вҖ”it spreads around like yeast in bread dough\+add*.\wj*
\v 2 \x + \xo 12:2: \xt Mrk 4:22; Luk 8:17.\x*\wj But everything that's coveredВҰ50191 up \+add now\+add*, will be uncovered \+add in the future\+add*, andВҰ50197 everything that's \+add now\+add* hiddenВҰ50198 will revealedВҰ50196.\wj*
\v 3 \wj Anything that you \+add whispered\+add* in the dark will be heardВҰ50214 in the lightВҰ50213, and anything that was only for certain ears in a privateВҰ50223 room will be announced from the rooftops.\wj*
\s1 Who to be afraid of
\rem /s1 Exhortation to Fearless Confession; Whom to Fear
\r (Mat. 10:28-31)
\p
\v 4 вҖң\wj And I'm telling you, myВҰ50233 friendsВҰ50232, that you shouldn'tВҰ50234 be afraidВҰ50236 of those who can kill your bodyВҰ50241 (andВҰ50229 afterВҰ50246 that they don'tВҰ50234 have anythingВҰ50256 more that they can do).\wj*
\v 5 \wj But I'll tell you who you should be afraid of: Be afraid of the one who has the authorityВҰ50270 to throwВҰ50272 you into hell afterВҰ50265 you're deadвҖ”yes, that's who you should be afraid of.\wj*
\p
\v 6 вҖң\wj Aren't fiveВҰ50285 small birds sold for just a couple of small coins? Yet not one of those birds is forgottenВҰ50298 by \+nd GodВҰ50301\+nd*.\wj*
\v 7 \wj Yes, \+add God\+add* even knows the numberВҰ50312 of hairsВҰ50305 on yourВҰ50310 head so don'tВҰ50315 worry, \+add each\+add* one of you is of more valueВҰ50322 than \+add a whole flock of\+add* birds.\wj*
\s1 Disowning the messiah
\rem /s1 Confessing and Rejecting Christ
\r (Mat. 10:32-33; 12:32; 10:19-20)
\p
\v 8 вҖң\wj I'm telling youВҰ50326 that everyoneВҰ50328 who admits in public to following me, so too humanity's child will tell their names to God's messengersВҰ50349,\wj*
\v 9 \wj butВҰ50353 anyone who disowns me in public will be disownedВҰ50354 in front of God's messengersВҰ50366.\wj*
\p
\v 10 \x + \xo 12:10: \xt Mrk 3:29; Mat 12:32.\x*вҖң\wj EveryoneВҰ50379 who says something against humanity's child will be forgiven, but those who speak against the holy \+nd spiritВҰ50390\+nd* won'tВҰ50393 be forgiven.\wj*
\p
\v 11 \x + \xo 12:11-12: \xt Mrk 13:11; Mat 10:19-20; Luk 21:14-15.\x*вҖң\wj Whenever you get dragged into the meetingВҰ50416 hallsВҰ50416 or in front of rulersВҰ50420 or authoritiesВҰ50423, don'tВҰ50426 worryВҰ50428 about how you'll defendВҰ50433 yourselves or what you'll sayВҰ50437,\wj*
\v 12 \wj becauseВҰ50439 the holy \+nd spiritВҰ50441\+nd* will show youВҰ50444 all the right thing to sayВҰ50451 at the right time.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The parable about accumulating wealth
\rem /s1 Story of the Rich Fool; The Parable of the Rich Fool
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ50453 someoneВҰ50454 in the crowdВҰ50458 saidВҰ50452, вҖңTeacherВҰ50460, tell myВҰ50464 brotherВҰ50463 to give me a share of our father's estate.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\wj Man,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ50472, вҖң\wj who saidВҰ50472 that I'm the judgeВҰ50478 or arbitratorВҰ50481 over youВҰ50483 all?\wj*вҖқ
\v 15 ThenВҰ50486 he told them, вҖң\wj Keep alert to avoid all greedinessВҰ50495, becauseВҰ50496 a person's lifeВҰ50504 is not about gaining lots of possessionsВҰ50511.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThenВҰ50516 he told them all this parableВҰ50517, вҖң\wj One time a rich man's farm produced a really good harvest.\wj*
\v 17 \wj SoВҰ50528 he started figuring out what to do, вҖҳWhat should I do? I don'tВҰ50537 have anywhere to store myВҰ50544 harvest.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 18 \wj вҖҳAh,вҖҷ he saidВҰ50546, вҖҳI know what I'll do. I'll knock down my barns and buildВҰ50558 bigger ones, and thenВҰ50545 I'll store all my grainВҰ50566 and other produce in thereВҰ50562.\wj*
\v 19 \wj ThenВҰ50573 I'll be able to tell myВҰ50577 soulВҰ50576: Soul, you've got enough goodВҰ50582 things now to be able to relax for many yearsВҰ50585 of restingВҰ50587, eating, drinkingВҰ50589, andВҰ50573 beingВҰ50590 happy.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 20 \wj But \+nd GodВҰ50596\+nd* saidВҰ50591 to himВҰ50593, вҖҳHow foolish! Tonight I'll be demanding yourВҰ50607 soulВҰ50603 and then who will everything you stored up go to?вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj So \+add that's the end\+add* of someone who accumulated so much for himselfВҰ50620, but wasn't rich in God's \+add eyes\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
