\p
\v 35 \x + \xo 12:35: \xt Mat 25:1-13.\x*вҖң\wj Get up and get dressed and get the lampsВҰ50909 burning\wj*
\v 36 \x + \xo 12:36: \xt Mrk 13:34-36.\x*\wj like someone who's waitingВҰ50915 for their masterВҰ50917. When he leaves the weddingВҰ50925 celebrations and comes and knocksВҰ50930, you'll be ready to immediatelyВҰ50932 open the door.\wj*
\v 37 \wj The \+nd masterВҰ50943\+nd* would bless the slavesВҰ50938 that are ready, watchingВҰ50946 for when he arrives. I can assure you that he'll dress himself and then he'll seat them on couches and come and serve them there himself.\wj*
\v 38 \wj If he arrives around midnight or even in the small hours of the morning, he'll find them ready. Yes, they'll be blessedВҰ50987.\wj*
\v 39 \x + \xo 12:39-40: \xt Mat 24:43-44.\x*\wj But you should also know this: if the home-owner knew what time the thiefВҰ51005 would arrive, he'd be ready watchingВҰ51007 andВҰ51009 not allowВҰ51012 hisВҰ51016 houseВҰ51015 to be burgled.\wj*
\v 40 \wj So you all need to be readyВҰ51022 becauseВҰ51023 you don'tВҰ51027 know when \+add I,\+add* humanity's child, am going to arrive.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Good and bad slaves
