\r (Mat. 16:2-3)
\p
\v 54 YeshuaВҰ51367 also told the crowdsВҰ51353, вҖң\wj WheneverВҰ51354 you seeВҰ51356 a cloudВҰ51358 comingВҰ51368 from the west, you all say that it's going to rain, andВҰ51350 sure enough it does.\wj*
\v 55 \wj Likewise if there's a windВҰ51374 from the southВҰ51374, youВҰ51378 all say that it's going to be a scorcherВҰ51381, andВҰ51384 sure enough it is.\wj*
\v 56 \wj HypocritesВҰ51386! You know how to interpret the skyВҰ51397 andВҰ51394 the ground, butВҰ51405 youВҰ51409 all don'tВҰ51408 know how to scrutiniseВҰ51411 this timeВҰ51404 period.\wj*
\s1 Facing up to your obligations
\rem /s1 Settle with Your Opponent; Settling with Your Opponent
\r (Mat. 5:25-26)
\p
\v 57 вҖң\wj Even for yourselvesВҰ51416, can'tВҰ51417 youВҰ51418 judge what is rightВҰ51420 \+add andВҰ51413 wrong\+add*?\wj*
\v 58 \wj BecauseВҰ51422 as you'reВҰ51423 on the way with yourВҰ51427 opponentВҰ51426 to an arbitrator, think \+add hard\+add* about how to resolve the case, becauseВҰ51422 if you don't, he might drag you off to the judge, and the judge will hand you over to the constable, and the constable will toss you into a prisonВҰ51468 cell.\wj*
\v 59 \wj I'm telling you that you won'tВҰ51472 get out of thereВҰ51474 untilВҰ51475 every last \+add вүҲpenny\+add* has been repaid.\wj*вҖқ
\c 13
\s1 Turn from your sins so you won't perish
\rem /s1 Turn from Your Sins or Die; Repent or Perish; A Call to Repentance
\p
\v 1 There were some people there at the timeВҰ51492 who'd reportedВҰ51493 to Yeshua that \add Governor\add* PilateВҰ51501 had \add killed\add* some GalileansВҰ51497 when they were sacrificingВҰ51505.
\v 2 Yeshua asked the people, вҖң\wj Do you think that theseВҰ51518 Galileans were the most disobedient to God in all Galilee that theyВҰ51529 were made to sufferВҰ51529 so much?\wj*
\v 3 \wj No, I'm telling you all, but on the other hand if you don'tВҰ51535 turn from your own disobedience and request forgiveness, you all will perishВҰ51541 likewiseВҰ51539.\wj*
\v 4 \wj What about thoseВҰ51543 eighteenВҰ51545 who were killedВҰ51561 when the SiloamВҰ51558 towerВҰ51554 collapsed on them? Do youВҰ51563 think theyВҰ51565 had bigger debts than all the peopleВҰ51572 livingВҰ51575 in Yerushalem?\wj*
\v 5 \wj No, I'm telling you all that if you don'tВҰ51586 turn from your own disobedience and request forgiveness, you all will perishВҰ51593 likewiseВҰ51592.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The parable about the tree without fruit
