\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ51595 Yeshua told \add them\add* this parableВҰ51598, вҖң\wj There was a \+add landowner\+add* who'd plantedВҰ51603 a figВҰ51599 treeВҰ51599 in hisВҰ51607 vineyardВҰ51606, andВҰ51595 he wentВҰ51610 to see if it had any fruitВҰ51612 on it, but there wasn't any\wj*
\v 7 \wj so he told his manager, вҖҳI've been comingВҰ51634 andВҰ51624 checking for fruitВҰ51636 on this treeВҰ51639 for threeВҰ51629 yearsВҰ51630, but there's none. Chop it down becauseВҰ51650 it's not good use of the land.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 8 \wj вҖҳMasterВҰ51663,вҖҷ he answeredВҰ51660, вҖҳgive me one more yearВҰ51673 to dig aroundВҰ51678 it andВҰ51659 fertilise it\wj*
\v 9 \wj and see if it fruitsВҰ51691. If it doesn't, then certainly you can chop it down.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
