\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ51997 Yeshua started on his journeyВҰ52007 towardsВҰ52010 Yerushalem, andВҰ51997 as he passed throughВҰ51998 each town or villageВҰ52002, he would teachВҰ52003 \add the people there\add*,
\v 23 andВҰ52013 \add one day\add* someoneВҰ52014 asked himВҰ52015, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ52016\nd*, will only a few \add people\add* be savedВҰ52021?вҖқ
\p Yeshua replied,
\v 24 \wj Make an effort to get in throughВҰ52030 the narrowВҰ52032 doorВҰ52033, becauseВҰ52036 I'm telling you that many people want to come in but they won'tВҰ52043 be able to.\wj*
\v 25 \wj Once the home-owner gets up and locks the door, even if you \+add get there now and\+add* stand outsideВҰ52061 knockingВҰ52064 and calling out, вҖҳMasterВҰ52068, open up for us,вҖҷ he'll answerВҰ52073, вҖҳI don'tВҰ52076 know you or whereВҰ52079 you're from.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 26 \wj вҖҳYou saw us eating and drinking,вҖҷ you'll start sayingВҰ52084, and, вҖҳYou taughtВҰ52096 along ourВҰ52095 roadsВҰ52094.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 27 \x + \xo 13:27: \xt Psa 6:8.\x*\wj ButВҰ52097 he'll reply to you all, вҖҳI've got no idea whereВҰ52107 you're all from, so go away you who do evil deeds.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 28 \x + \xo 13:28: \xt Mat 22:13; 25:30.\x*\wj There'llВҰ52118 be crying and much anguish when you all seeВҰ52128 AbrahamВҰ52131 and Isaak and YacobВҰ52135 and all the prophetsВҰ52139 in God's kingdomВҰ52142, but all of you will be beingВҰ52148 thrownВҰ52148 out.\wj*
\v 29 \wj Others will come from the east and the west, and from the northВҰ52158 and the southВҰ52160, and \+em they\+em* will be comfortably seated in God's kingdomВҰ52165,\wj*
\v 30 \x + \xo 13:30: \xt Mrk 10:31; Mat 19:30; 20:16.\x*\wj so listen: the last \+add people\+add* will be the first ones, andВҰ52176 the first ones will end up last.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's concern for Yerushalem
\rem /s1 The Lament over Jerusalem; Jesus Grieves over Jerusalem; Jesus' Sorrow for Jerusalem; Jesus' Love for Jerusalem
\r (Mat. 23:37-39)
\p
\v 31 At that time, some members of the Pharisee partyВҰ52193 approachedВҰ52189 Yeshua andВҰ52198 told himВҰ52196, вҖңYou need to leave here becauseВҰ52201 HerodВҰ52202 wants to killВҰ52207 youВҰ52205.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 Yeshua respondedВҰ52209, вҖң\wj Go and tell that fox: вҖҳI'm drivingВҰ52217 out demonsВҰ52218 and healingВҰ52220 \+add people\+add* todayВҰ52226 and tomorrowВҰ52228, but I'll be finishedВҰ52222 the following day.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 33 \wj Yes, I need to keep moving todayВҰ52238 and tomorrowВҰ52241, becauseВҰ52247 it wouldn't do for a prophetВҰ52251 to come to his end away from Yerushalem.\wj*
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj Yerushalem, YerushalemвҖ”the cityВҰ52258 that kills the prophetsВҰ52261 and throwsВҰ52263 rocksВҰ52263 at those who've been sentВҰ52265 to her. How oftenВҰ52269 I wanted to gatherВҰ52271 yourВҰ52274 childrenВҰ52273 togetherВҰ52271 like a hen gathersВҰ52277 her chicks underВҰ52285 her wingsВҰ52287, but you all didn'tВҰ52289 want it.\wj*
\v 35 \x + \xo 13:35: \xt Psa 118:26.\x*\wj \+add SoВҰ52300 now,\+add* see, yourВҰ52296 temple will be left \+add without a congregation\+add*. I'm telling you all that you certainly won'tВҰ52305 see me \+add again\+add* untilВҰ52309 you sayВҰ52315: вҖҳBlessed is the \+add person\+add* who comes in the nameВҰ52320 \+add andВҰ52300 authority\+add* of \+nd YahwehВҰ52321\+nd*.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
