\v 1 One dayВҰ52338, Yeshua went to the houseВҰ52331 of one of the Pharisee partyВҰ52336 leaders for a meal on a Rest Day, andВҰ52322 they were watchingВҰ52344 him closelyВҰ52344.
\v 2 ThenВҰ52346, look, there was a manВҰ52348 there with badly swollen limbs.
\v 3 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded \add to the thoughts of\add* the lawyersВҰ52362 andВҰ52363 Pharisees by asking, вҖң\wj Is itВҰ52367 allowable to healВҰ52371 on the Rest Day or not?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 4 However, they \add just\add* stayed silent, so heВҰ52379 took hold of the man and healedВҰ52379 him and sentВҰ52383 him away.
\v 5 \x + \xo 14:5: \xt Mat 12:11.\x*ThenВҰ52384 he asked them, вҖң\wj Which of you if your child or your animal fell into a pit wouldn't immediatelyВҰ52413 pull them out, even if it was a Rest Day?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 6 ButВҰ52424 theyВҰ52427 didn'tВҰ52426 have any answerВҰ52430 for that.
\s1 Demonstrating humility
\rem /s1 Humility and Hospitality; Jesus Teaches about Humility
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ52435 he told a parableВҰ52440 to all the invitedВҰ52439 guests after he'd noticedВҰ52441 them choosingВҰ52445 the best placesВҰ52444 around the table, telling them,
\v 8 \x + \xo 14:8-10: \xt Prv 25:6-7.\x*вҖң\wj WheneverВҰ52449 you're invited to a weddingВҰ52454 celebration, don'tВҰ52456 go and sit in the best placeВҰ52461, in case someone more important than you might be called over by the host,\wj*
\v 9 \wj and then your host might comeВҰ52471 over to you and ask you to let the other guest sit where you were, and then you might end up humiliated at the bottom of the table.\wj*
\v 10 \wj Rather, when you're invitedВҰ52507, sitВҰ52497 down at the end so that the host might comeВҰ52505 and tell you, вҖҳFriendВҰ52512, move up here to a better spot.вҖҷ Then you'll be honoured in front of all the other guests,\wj*
\v 11 \x + \xo 14:11: \xt Mat 23:12; Luk 18:14.\x*\wj because the person who thinks a lot of themself will be humbled, andВҰ52535 the person who humbles themself will be honoured.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ52542 Yeshua also spoke to the man who had invited himВҰ52546, вҖң\wj WheneverВҰ52547 you host a brunch or dinnerВҰ52550, don'tВҰ52553 invite your friendsВҰ52556 or siblings, or your \+add other\+add* relativesВҰ52564 or your wealthyВҰ52571 neighboursВҰ52568, because they can invite you back andВҰ52542 so repayВҰ52582 you.\wj*
\v 13 \wj Instead when you're celebrating, invite the poor and the crippledВҰ52592, the lame and the blindВҰ52594,\wj*
\v 14 \wj and then you'll be rewarded \+add by God\+add* becauseВҰ52598 those \+add people\+add* won'tВҰ52599 be able to repayВҰ52601 you, hence you'll be repaidВҰ52603 \+add instead\+add* when those who please God come back to life.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The parable about the reluctant dinner guests
