\r (Mat. 22:1-10)
\p
\v 15 Now one of the people at the meal heardВҰ52612 all this andВҰ52613 commented, вҖңBlessedВҰ52621 is anyoneВҰ52614 who gets to have a meal in God's kingdomВҰ52629.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 But Yeshua respondedВҰ52635, вҖң\wj There was a home-owner who was putting on a large dinner andВҰ52645 invitedВҰ52646 many \+add people\+add*.\wj*
\v 17 \wj When the meal was ready, he sentВҰ52649 out hisВҰ52652 slaveВҰ52651 to go andВҰ52648 tell everyone who'd been invitedВҰ52659, вҖҳCome over now becauseВҰ52661 the food is ready.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 18 \wj However they all started giving excuses. The firstВҰ52677 one saidВҰ52678, вҖҳI boughtВҰ52681 a fieldВҰ52680 and I need to go and inspect itВҰ52691. Please excuse me.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 19 \wj Another one saidВҰ52700, вҖҳI've boughtВҰ52703 fiveВҰ52705 pairsВҰ52701 of oxen andВҰ52706 I need to check them out. Please excuseВҰ52718 me.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 20 \wj Yet anotherВҰ52721 saidВҰ52722, вҖҳI just got marriedВҰ52725 so I can'tВҰ52731 really comeВҰ52733.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 21 \wj SoВҰ52734 when the slave got back, he reportedВҰ52739 all this to hisВҰ52743 masterВҰ52741. The home-owner got angry and told the slave, вҖҳWell thenВҰ52734, hurry out into the roadsВҰ52760 and streetsВҰ52762 of the cityВҰ52764 and bringВҰ52780 back the poor and crippledВҰ52772 and blindВҰ52775 and lame people.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 22 \wj \+add When he'd done that,\+add* the slaveВҰ52786 saidВҰ52783, вҖҳMasterВҰ52788, I've done what youВҰ52792 instructedВҰ52792 andВҰ52793 there'sВҰ52796 stillВҰ52794 roomВҰ52795 \+add at the table\+add*.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 23 \wj SoВҰ52797 the masterВҰ52800 instructed him, вҖҳWell go along the roadsВҰ52809 and fencesВҰ52812 and force them to comeВҰ52816 so that myВҰ52819 houseВҰ52821 will fill up,\wj*
\v 24 \wj becauseВҰ52824 I'm telling youВҰ52825 thatВҰ52832 none of thoseВҰ52831 invitedВҰ52833 guests will get a taste of this meal of mine.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\s1 Count the cost of following Yeshua
