\p
\v 25 Large crowdsВҰ52849 were following Yeshua when heВҰ52853 turnedВҰ52852 andВҰ52851 spoke to them,
\v 26 \x + \xo 14:26: \xt Mat 10:37.\x*вҖң\wj If anyoneВҰ52858 comes to me but doesn't \+add love me more than they love\+add* their parents and their siblings, and their spouse and childrenВҰ52879, and even their own lifeВҰ52892, then that person is unable to become myВҰ52897 apprenticeВҰ52899.\wj*
\v 27 \x + \xo 14:27: \xt Mrk 8:34; Mat 10:38; 16:24; Luk 9:23.\x*\wj Anyone who doesn't give up everything in this life andВҰ52911 come afterВҰ52913 me is unable to become myВҰ52918 apprenticeВҰ52920,\wj*
\v 28 \wj becauseВҰ52924 none of you would want to buildВҰ52931 a towerВҰ52930 without firstВҰ52933 countingВҰ52936 the cost and figuring out if you'll have enoughВҰ52940 to completeВҰ52944 it.\wj*
\v 29 \wj Otherwise you might lay the foundationВҰ52950 and not be able to finishВҰ52956 it. Then everyone watching might beginВҰ52962 to mock\wj*
\v 30 \wj andВҰ52974 say, вҖҳThis person started a buildingВҰ52973 project but wasn't able to finishВҰ52977 itВҰ52977.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 31 \wj Or what king would go off to war against anotherВҰ52983 king, if he hadn't previously sat down with his \+add generals\+add* to figure out if their ten thousand \+add soldiers\+add* are powerfulВҰ52997 enough to battle the other king bringing twentyВҰ53007 thousand against him?\wj*
\v 32 \wj If they can'tВҰ53015, thenВҰ53014 while \+add the other army\+add* is stillВҰ53017 far away, the king will send ahead a delegationВҰ53022 to try to make peaceВҰ53029.\wj*
