\c 15
\s1 The lost sheep that was found
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Lost Sheep; Finding the lost; Story of the Lost Sheep
\r (Mat. 18:12-14)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 15:1-2: \xt Luk 5:29-30.\x*Many tax-collectors andВҰ53094 \add others regarded as\add* sinnersВҰ53096 had come closer so they could hearВҰ53097 what Yeshua \add was teaching\add*,
\v 2 but those from the Pharisee partyВҰ53103 and the religiousВҰ53108 teachersВҰ53108 were grumblingВҰ53100, вҖңThis manВҰ53111 acceptsВҰ53113 sinnersВҰ53112 and \add even\add* eats with them!вҖқ
\v 3 SoВҰ53118 Yeshua told them this parableВҰ53122:
\p
\v 4 вҖң\wj If you had a hundredВҰ53132 sheep and one of them went missing, which of you wouldn't leave the ninety-nine there in the wildernessВҰ53149 and go and search for the missing sheep untilВҰ53157 you found it?\wj*
\v 5 \wj And once you foundВҰ53162 it, you would carry it home on your shouldersВҰ53166 feeling very happy.\wj*
\v 6 \wj When you got back to the houseВҰ53176, \+add surely\+add* you'd call your friendsВҰ53180 and neighboursВҰ53183 and tell them, вҖҳCome and celebrate with me becauseВҰ53188 I foundВҰ53189 myВҰ53192 lost sheepВҰ53191.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 7 \wj I'm telling youВҰ53197 all that there's similar celebration in heavenВҰ53204 when one person \+add turns from their disobedience and obeys God\+add*вҖ”more than over ninety-nine guiltless people who have no need to change.\wj*
\s1 The lost coin that was found
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Lost Coin; Story of the Lost Coin
\p
\v 8 вҖң\wj Or what womanВҰ53223 who had tenВҰ53227 silver coins and lost one, wouldn't lightВҰ53235 a lamp and sweepВҰ53238 the houseВҰ53240 and search thoroughly untilВҰ53244 she found it?\wj*
\v 9 \wj ThenВҰ53248 she'd invite her friendsВҰ53253 and neighboursВҰ53256 sayingВҰ53259, вҖҳCome and celebrate with me becauseВҰ53262 I found the money that I'd lost.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 10 \wj I'm telling youВҰ53271 all that there'sВҰ53272 similar celebration by God's messengersВҰ53278 \+add in heaven\+add* over one person who \+add turns from their disobedience and obeys God\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The parable about the returning son
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Prodigal and His Brother; The Parable of the Lost Son; Story of the Lost Son
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ53287 Yeshua told \add them\add*, вҖң\wj Once there was a manВҰ53288 with twoВҰ53292 sonsВҰ53293.\wj*
\v 12 \wj The youngerВҰ53298 son asked his father to give him his inheritance \+add in advance\+add*, so the father dividedВҰ53315 everything up.\wj*
\v 13 \wj ThenВҰ53319 a few daysВҰ53324 later, that youngerВҰ53330 son went off to a distantВҰ53335 countryВҰ53334 where he used hisВҰ53343 inheritance to enjoy an affluent andВҰ53319 carefree lifestyle.\wj*
\v 14 \wj However after he'd used up all hisВҰ53353 funds, a terrible famineВҰ53356 hit that countryВҰ53362, and he started to become needy,\wj*
\v 15 \wj so he went andВҰ53369 signed up to work for one of the local farmers who assigned him to feed the pigs out in the fieldsВҰ53383.\wj*
\v 16 \wj As the pigs were eatingВҰ53400 their carobВҰ53398 pods, their food started to look desirableВҰ53388 to him, but he wasn't given any.\wj*
\v 17 \wj But he \+add eventually\+add* came to his senses and said to himselfВҰ53409, вҖҳEven myВҰ53419 father'sВҰ53418 workers have plentyВҰ53421 of food, but here I am in this place dying of starvation.\wj*
\v 18 \wj I'm goingВҰ53432 to leave and go \+add back\+add* to myВҰ53436 father to tell him, вҖңFather, I've disobeyed \+add God\+add* and \+add вүЎdishonoured\+add* you\wj*
\v 19 \wj and I'm no longerВҰ53449 worthyВҰ53451 to be calledВҰ53452 your son. Take me on as one of your workers.вҖқ вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 20 вҖң\wj SoВҰ53464 he gotВҰ53465 upВҰ53465 and headed back to his father, butВҰ53473 his father saw him coming from a distance and felt sorry for him. He ran and hugged \+add his son\+add* and kissedВҰ53494 him,\wj*
\v 21 \wj and the son saidВҰ53496, вҖҳFather, I've disobeyed \+add God\+add* and \+add вүЎdishonoured\+add* you and I'm no longerВҰ53513 worthyВҰ53515 to be calledВҰ53516 yourВҰ53518 son.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 22 \wj But the fatherВҰ53530 ordered his slavesВҰ53533, вҖҳQuicklyВҰ53537, bringВҰ53539 out the best robeВҰ53542 and dressВҰ53546 him in it, and put a ring on his handВҰ53554 and sandalsВҰ53557 on his feetВҰ53560.\wj*
\v 23 \wj Then get the grain-fed calf and slaughter itВҰ53572 so weВҰ53577 can celebrate with a feast,\wj*
\v 24 \wj because myВҰ53583 son was deadВҰ53585 but he's now here aliveвҖ”he was lost but now he's foundВҰ53596.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 25 вҖң\wj The man's older son was \+add out working\+add* in a fieldВҰ53609, and when he was heading home and got near the houseВҰ53620, he could hear \+add the sound of\+add* musicВҰ53622 and dancingВҰ53625\wj*
\v 26 \wj so he calledВҰ53627 out to one of the servantsВҰ53630 andВҰ53626 asked him what was going on.\wj*
\v 27 \wj вҖҳYourВҰ53647 brotherВҰ53646 has come home,вҖҷ he replied, вҖҳandВҰ53641 yourВҰ53647 fatherВҰ53652 has slaughtered the grain-fed calf \+add to celebrate\+add* becauseВҰ53660 he got back safely.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 28 \wj ButВҰ53672 the \+add older\+add* son was angry and didn'tВҰ53667 want to go in, however hisВҰ53675 fatherВҰ53674 came out and imploredВҰ53677 him \+add to join them\+add*.\wj*
\v 29 \wj вҖҳListenВҰ53687,вҖҷ saidВҰ53683 \+add the older son\+add* to hisВҰ53686 fatherВҰ53685, вҖҳI've worked for you for however many yearsВҰ53689 andВҰ53681 I've never disobeyed you, yet you never gaveВҰ53702 me even a youngВҰ53704 goatВҰ53704 so that I could celebrate with myВҰ53712 friendsВҰ53711!\wj*
\v 30 \wj Yet when \+em this\+em* son of yours comes home after using up yourВҰ53721 money livingВҰ53730 with prostitutesВҰ53733, then you slaughter the fattened calf for himВҰ53738!вҖҷ\wj*
\v 31 \wj вҖҳSon,вҖҷ answered the father, вҖҳyouВҰ53749 have alwaysВҰ53750 been here with me, andВҰ53754 everything I have is yoursВҰ53758.\wj*
\v 32 \wj But it's right to be happy and excited, becauseВҰ53766 yourВҰ53769 brotherВҰ53768 was deadВҰ53771 and now he's alive \+add againВҰ53774\+add*вҖ”he was lost and now he's foundВҰ53780.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\c 16
\s1 The parable about the shrewd manager
\rem /s1 Story of the Shrewd Manager; The Parable of the Dishonest Manager; The Parable of the Shrewd Manager; Instructing the disciples
\p
\v 1 Yeshua also told this to hisВҰ53806 followers, вҖң\wj Once there was a rich manВҰ53789 who had a manager who worked for him. A whistle-blower reported that the manager had been abusing the owner's possessionsВҰ53805\wj*
\v 2 \wj so the owner calledВҰ53808 him andВҰ53807 asked, вҖҳWhat'sВҰ53812 this I'm hearingВҰ53814 about you? Give back the ledgers becauseВҰ53824 I don'tВҰ53823 want you as a managerВҰ53821 any more.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 3 \wj ThenВҰ53831 the manager thought to himselfВҰ53833, вҖҳ\+add Oh dear,\+add* what will I do now that I'm losing this management job? I'm not \+add strong enough to be out\+add* diggingВҰ53848 andВҰ53831 I'd be too ashamedВҰ53853 to beg.\wj*
\v 4 \wj I know what I'll do so that when I lose my job, I'll still be popular with everyone else.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 5 \wj SoВҰ53871 he calledВҰ53872 in each person who owed money to his master. He asked the firstВҰ53884 one, вҖҳHow much do you owe myВҰ53889 master?вҖҷ\wj*
\v 6 \wj вҖҳA hundredВҰ53894 jugs of oliveВҰ53897 oil,вҖҷ he replied. вҖҳWell, bring the contract here andВҰ53891 change it quicklyВҰ53912 to fiftyВҰ53915,вҖҷ the manager said.\wj*
\v 7 \wj ThenВҰ53921 he asked the next one, вҖҳHow much do you owe?вҖҷ вҖҳA hundredВҰ53927 containers of wheatВҰ53929,вҖҷ the man replied. вҖҳGet the contract form andВҰ53921 change it to eightyВҰ53944,вҖҷ said the manager.\wj*
\v 8 \wj \+add When he heard,\+add* the landowner praisedВҰ53946 the dishonest managerВҰ53950 for his shrewdness becauseВҰ53953 the modern generation are better at working the system than the children of lightВҰ53971 in their generation.\wj*
\p
\v 9 вҖң\wj SoВҰ53980 I'm telling you all to use worldly moneyВҰ53992 to make friendsВҰ53988 for yourselvesВҰ53986, so that wheneverВҰ53996 it runs out, they'll accept you all into the eternalВҰ54005 homes.\f + \fr 16:9 \ft This sentence is very difficult to understand, so it's likely that we're missing some cultural cues here, and in the parable above.\f*\wj*
\v 10 \wj Anyone who's faithful with a little is also faithful with much, andВҰ54016 the person who's dishonest with a little is also dishonest with a lot.\wj*
\v 11 \wj Because of that, if you aren'tВҰ54035 faithfulВҰ54034 with worldly moneyВҰ54033, who would entrustВҰ54041 true wealthВҰ54038 to you all?\wj*
\v 12 \wj If you're not faithfulВҰ54047 in your treatment of strangersВҰ54046, who would give you anything for yourselves?\wj*
\p
\v 13 \x + \xo 16:13: \xt Mat 6:24.\x*вҖң\wj No householdВҰ54058 servantВҰ54058 can serve twoВҰ54060 mastersВҰ54061, becauseВҰ54065 eitherВҰ54064 they'll hate the one and love the other, or they'll support the one and despiseВҰ54079 the other.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 More of Yeshua's teaching
\rem /s1 The Law and the Kingdom of God; Some Sayings of Jesus
\r (Mark 10:11-12; Mat. 11:12-13)
\rem /r (Matthew 11.12,13; 5.31,32; Mark 10.11,12)
\p
\v 14 All those from the Pharisee partyВҰ54092 were listening carefully because they love moneyВҰ54093, andВҰ54087 they were sneeringВҰ54096 at Yeshua,
\v 15 so he said to them, вҖң\wj You all justifyВҰ54104 yourselvesВҰ54105 to the people but God knows yourВҰ54115 heartsВҰ54114, becauseВҰ54116 what people value most is abhorrent to God.\wj*
\rem /s1 Additional Teachings
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 16:16: \xt Mat 11:12-13.\x*вҖң\wj The Hebrew scriptures \+add applied\+add* untilВҰ54133 Yohan-the-immerser started preachingВҰ54144 the goodВҰ54144 messageВҰ54144 about God's kingdomВҰ54141, now everyoneВҰ54146 is striving to get into itВҰ54148,\wj*\f + \fr 16:16 \ft See https://rediscoveryingjesus.substack.com/p/jesuss-confusing-sayings-luke-1616.\f*
\v 17 \x + \xo 16:17: \xt Mat 5:18.\x*\wj butВҰ54151 it's easierВҰ54150 for the sky andВҰ54155 the earthВҰ54157 to disappear than it is for one small part of the law to fall.\wj*
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 16:18: \xt Mat 5:32; 1Cor 7:10-11.\x*вҖң\wj EveryВҰ54167 man who dismisses hisВҰ54172 wifeВҰ54171 and marries anotherВҰ54175 is committing adultery, and the one marrying the woman he dismissed is committing adultery.\wj*
\s1 The rich man and Lazarus
\rem /s1 The Rich Man and Lazarus
\p
\v 19 вҖң\wj Once there was a rich manВҰ54186 who dressedВҰ54199 like a king and had everythingВҰ54205 in life to make him happy and content.\wj*
\v 20 \wj At the same time there was a poor \+add beggar\+add* named LazarusВҰ54213 who was covered in ulcersВҰ54220. He'd been carried to the rich man's gateВҰ54218\wj*,
\v 21 \wj \+add where he lay\+add*, hoping to get any food thatВҰ54229 might fall off the rich man's tableВҰ54235. The dogs even came and licked hisВҰ54248 ulcersВҰ54247,\wj*
\v 22 \wj and \+add eventually\+add* he died and was carriedВҰ54257 away by \+add God's messengersВҰ54261\+add* to \+add recline at the table\+add* next to AbrahamВҰ54266. ThenВҰ54250 the rich man also died and was buriedВҰ54276\wj*
\v 23 \wj and was tormentedВҰ54287 in hell. HoweverВҰ54280, when he looked up, he saw AbrahamВҰ54290 in the distance and LazarusВҰ54294 \+add reclining next\+add* to him\wj*,
\v 24 \wj so he calledВҰ54305 out, вҖҳFather AbrahamВҰ54308, be merciful to me and sendВҰ54312 LazarusВҰ54313 \+add here\+add* to dip the tip of hisВҰ54320 fingerВҰ54319 in waterВҰ54321 and cool down myВҰ54327 tongueВҰ54326, becauseВҰ54328 I'm very distressedВҰ54329 \+add here\+add* in this flameВҰ54332.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 25 \wj But AbrahamВҰ54336 replied, вҖҳSon, don't forget that you enjoyed the goodВҰ54344 lifeВҰ54349 while you were alive, whereas LazarusВҰ54352 had it bad, butВҰ54335 now he's here being comfortedВҰ54360 and you'reВҰ54361 suffering.\wj*
\v 26 \wj Anyway, there's a deep chasmВҰ54375 that's been establishedВҰ54377 betweenВҰ54369 us, so that anyone here who wanted to go to you can'tВҰ54386, nor can anyone from there crossВҰ54395 over here to us.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 27 \wj вҖҳI have one request thenВҰ54399,вҖҷ saidВҰ54397 the man \+add who'd been rich\+add*. вҖҳSend Lazarus to myВҰ54414 father's houseВҰ54411\wj*,
\v 28 \wj becauseВҰ54416 I have fiveВҰ54417 brothersВҰ54418. Then he can warn them about this placeВҰ54430 of tormentВҰ54433 so that they won'tВҰ54423 also comeВҰ54426 here.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 29 \wj вҖҳThey have the scriptures,вҖҷ answered AbrahamВҰ54439, вҖҳso they can find out what they say.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 30 \wj ButВҰ54448 the man insisted, вҖҳNo, fatherВҰ54451 AbrahamВҰ54453, butВҰ54454 if someoneВҰ54456 from the deadВҰ54459 went to them, thenВҰ54448 they'd turn from their sins.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 31 \wj вҖҳ\+add Well,\+add* if they ignore the scriptures,вҖҷ he answered, вҖҳeven if someoneВҰ54478 from the deadВҰ54480 went to them, they still wouldn't be persuadedВҰ54489.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\c 17
