\rem /s1 Teachings about Forgiveness and Faith; Some Sayings of Jesus; Sin, Faith, Duty
\r (Mark 9:42; Mat. 18:6-7,21-22)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ54491 Yeshua told hisВҰ54495 followers, вҖң\wj It's impossibleВҰ54496 thatВҰ54498 temptationsВҰ54502 will disappear, but a bad future awaits whoever brings them.\wj*
\v 2 \wj It would be better if that person had a heavy weight tied to them andВҰ54527 got thrownВҰ54528 into the seaВҰ54532 than if they cause a \+add younger\+add* one to stumbleВҰ54535.\wj*
\v 3 \x + \xo 17:3: \xt Mat 18:15.\x*\wj Take great care.\wj*
\p \wj If a fellow-believer disobeys God, scold them, and then if they stop and request forgiveness, forgiveВҰ54558 them.\wj*
\v 4 \wj \+add Even\+add* if they wrong you seven times in a dayВҰ54564 and thenВҰ54560 seven times come and tell you that they're turning away from it, forgiveВҰ54581 them.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Growing faith
\rem /s1 Faith
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ54585 the apprentices requested the \nd masterВҰ54590\nd*, вҖңGive us more faithВҰ54594.вҖқ
\v 6 вҖң\wj If you all had faithВҰ54605 like a \+add small\+add* mustardВҰ54608 seed,\wj*вҖқ the \nd masterВҰ54600\nd* replied, вҖң\wj you would be able to order a mulberryВҰ54614 bush, вҖҳGet out of the ground and plantВҰ54627 yourself in the seaВҰ54632,вҖҷ and itВҰ54635 would obey you all.\wj*
\s1 The work of a slave
\rem /s1 A Servant's Duty
\p
\v 7 вҖң\wj Imagine that you had a slaveВҰ54643 that was out in the fieldВҰ54652 ploughing or looking after the sheep. When he came back to the house, whichВҰ54638 of you would tell him, вҖҳ\+add The meal's ready so\+add* come in now andВҰ54639 sit down to eat.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 8 \wj No, you'd be sayingВҰ54663, вҖҳGet the meal ready for me and then after you've changed, come and wait on me as I eat and drink, then after that you can eat and drink.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 9 \wj And no, slavesВҰ54693 don'tВҰ54688 get thankedВҰ54691 for just doing what they've been told to do.\wj*
\v 10 \wj So too when you all do what you've been told to do, just say, вҖҳWe're useless slavesВҰ54716вҖ”we've just done what we were told.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua heals ten men with skin diseases
\rem /s1 Ten Healed of Leprosy; Jesus Heals Ten Men; Jesus Cleanses Ten Lepers
\p
\v 11 Soon itВҰ54727 was timeВҰ54729 to continue on towards Yerushalem and so they walked throughВҰ54736 GalileeВҰ54743 and ShomronВҰ54741 \add (SamariaВҰ54741)\add*.
\v 12 In one villageВҰ54749, they came across tenВҰ54755 menВҰ54757 with leprosyВҰ54756, who stoodВҰ54761 back at a distance
\v 13 andВҰ54765 called out, вҖң\nd YeshuaВҰ54774\nd*, masterВҰ54775, show mercyВҰ54776 to us.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 17:14: \xt Lev 14:1-32.\x*When he saw them, Yeshua called back, вҖң\wj Go and ask the priestsВҰ54793 to inspect you.\wj*вҖқ \add SoВҰ54778 they went off,\add* and as they were walking, they were healed.
\v 15 One of them, seeing that his skin was healedВҰ54808, came back andВҰ54803 could be heard loudlyВҰ54814 praising \nd GodВҰ54818\nd*,
\v 16 and he knelt down in front of Yeshua and thankedВҰ54828 him. This man was from ShomronВҰ54834.
\v 17 вҖң\wj Weren't there tenВҰ54859 of you that were healed?\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* asked. вҖң\wj Where's the \+add other\+add* nineВҰ54864?\wj*
\v 18 \wj Have none of them returnedВҰ54872 to praise \+nd GodВҰ54879\+nd*вҖ”only this foreignerВҰ54883?\wj*вҖқ
\v 19 ThenВҰ54885 he told him, вҖң\wj Get up andВҰ54885 go \+add now\+add*. YourВҰ54893 faithВҰ54892 has healedВҰ54894 you.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 God's kingdom
\rem /s1 The Coming of the Kingdom of God
\r (Mat. 24:23-28,37-41)
\p
\v 20 One time Yeshua was \add approached\add* by some from the Pharisee partyВҰ54900 and askedВҰ54896 when God's kingdom is coming, and he answeredВҰ54908, вҖң\wj The arrival of God's kingdom is not some visible thing,\wj*
\v 21 \wj and they won't be shouting, вҖҳLookВҰ54923, here it is!вҖҷ or вҖҳThereВҰ54928 it is!вҖҷ, becauseВҰ54932 you seeВҰ54931, God's kingdomВҰ54934 is insideВҰ54937 you all.\wj*вҖқ
\p
