\v 3 He wanted to see who \add this\add* \nd Yeshua\nd* was, but couldn't see over the crowdВҰ56122 because he\f + \fr 19:3 \ft It's commonly assumed that Zacchaeus was the short person in this sentence, but the Greek is ambiguous. (See https://www.biblicalarchaeology.org/daily/biblical-topics/new-testament/jesus-the-short-king/.)\f* was rather short,
\v 4 so he ran along ahead \add of the crowd\add* andВҰ56128 climbed a sycamoreВҰ56137 treeВҰ56137 so that he could seeВҰ56140 Yeshua as he walked past.
\v 5 However, as \nd Yeshua\nd* came to that place, he lookedВҰ56159 up and said, вҖң\wj Zacchaeus, hurry up and get down becauseВҰ56176 I think it would be good to stay at yourВҰ56180 place.\wj*вҖқ
\v 6 SoВҰ56184 heВҰ56187 hurriedВҰ56185 down \add the tree\add* andВҰ56188 happily welcomedВҰ56189 himВҰ56190.
\p
\v 7 ButВҰ56192 everyone who had observed itВҰ56193 was grumblingВҰ56196, вҖң\add Hoy,\add* he's going to stay with a sinfulВҰ56201 manВҰ56202.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \add At dinner,\add* Zacchaeus stoodВҰ56205 and said to the master, вҖңListenВҰ56213, master, I'm giving half of everything I own to the poor, and anyoneВҰ56230 that I defraudedВҰ56232, I'll pay them back four times over.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖң\wj Salvation came to this home today,\wj*вҖқ respondedВҰ56235 \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\wj as this man has also \+add shown that\+add* he's Abraham's offspring,\wj*
