\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ56269 Yeshua went on to tell a parableВҰ56274 to those who heard all that, becauseВҰ56275 he was getting near to Yerushalem andВҰ56269 they had assumed that God's kingdomВҰ56294 was goingВҰ56292 appearВҰ56298 straight away.
\v 12 Because of that, heВҰ56299 told them, вҖң\wj Once a manВҰ56302 of high status was going to a distantВҰ56311 countryВҰ56310 to inherit a kingdomВҰ56314, andВҰ56315 then to returnВҰ56316 \+add after that\+add*.\wj*
\v 13 \wj SoВҰ56318 he calledВҰ56317 his ten slavesВҰ56320 and gaveВҰ56323 them ten silverВҰ56326 coins and told them to put them to work until he got back.\wj*
\v 14 \wj But hisВҰ56341 citizensВҰ56340 hated him and sentВҰ56346 a delegationВҰ56347 out to him to say, вҖҳWe don'tВҰ56351 want this manВҰ56353 to reignВҰ56354 over us.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 15 вҖң\wj ButВҰ56357 he receivedВҰ56363 hisВҰ56362 kingdomВҰ56365 and thenВҰ56357 he headed back and sent for those slavesВҰ56372 that he had givenВҰ56376 the silverВҰ56378 to, to find out how \+add well\+add* they'd traded.\wj*
\v 16 \wj The firstВҰ56389 slave arrivedВҰ56386 andВҰ56387 said, вҖҳMasterВҰ56391, I used yourВҰ56394 silver coin to earn ten more coins.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 17 \wj вҖҳWell done goodВҰ56408 slaveВҰ56409,вҖҷ heВҰ56404 saidВҰ56404, вҖҳandВҰ56402 because you were faithfulВҰ56414 with a little, I'll put you in charge of tenВҰ56420 citiesВҰ56421.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 18 \wj ThenВҰ56422 the secondВҰ56425 \+add slave\+add* came andВҰ56422 said, вҖҳYourВҰ56433 silver masterВҰ56434, gained five more coins.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 19 \wj вҖҳYou too,вҖҷ \+add the master\+add* saidВҰ56439, вҖҳwill be put in charge of fiveВҰ56450 citiesВҰ56451.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 20 \wj ThenВҰ56452 anotherВҰ56454 \+add slave\+add* cameВҰ56455 andВҰ56452 said, вҖҳMasterВҰ56457, look, here's yourВҰ56461 silverВҰ56460 thatВҰ56462 I kept hidden away wrapped in a handkerchiefВҰ56466\wj*
\v 21 \wj becauseВҰ56472 I was scared of you, knowing that you'reВҰ56476 a hard manВҰ56473вҖ”picking up what you didn't put down, and harvesting where you didn't sow.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 22 \wj вҖҳI'll judge you by yourВҰ56496 own words,вҖҷ \+add the master\+add* said, вҖҳyou evilВҰ56499 slaveВҰ56500! You knew that I'm a hard manВҰ56504, picking up what I didn't put down, and harvesting what I didn't sow.\wj*
\v 23 \wj SoВҰ56518 why didn'tВҰ56522 youВҰ56523 take myВҰ56524 silverВҰ56526 to the bank? ThenВҰ56518 went I returned, at least I would have been able to collectВҰ56543 some interestВҰ56538.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 24 \wj ThenВҰ56545 \+add the master\+add* told the others who were standing there, вҖҳTake the silver coin away from him andВҰ56545 give it to the \+add slave\+add* who has the ten.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 25 \wj ButВҰ56564 theyВҰ56565 protested, вҖҳMasterВҰ56567, heВҰ56568 alreadyВҰ56570 has ten coins.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 19:26: \xt Mrk 4:25; Mat 13:12; Luk 8:18.\x*\wj вҖҳI'm telling youВҰ56573 all,вҖҷ \+add the master replied,\+add* вҖҳthat everyoneВҰ56575 who has, will be givenВҰ56579 \+add more\+add*, butВҰ56581 the person who doesn't have, even what they have will be takenВҰ56588 away \+add from them\+add*.\wj*
\v 27 \x + \xo 19:11-27: \xt Mat 25:14-30.\x*\wj HoweverВҰ56591, \+add about\+add* those enemiesВҰ56594 of mine who didn'tВҰ56599 want me to reignВҰ56603 over them: bringВҰ56607 them here andВҰ56609 strikeВҰ56610 them down in front of me.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua rides an unbroken colt into Yerushalem
