\r (Mark 12:1-12; Mat. 21:33-46)
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 20:9: \xt Isa 5:1.\x*ThenВҰ57213 Yeshua started telling this parableВҰ57221 to the peopleВҰ57216: вҖң\wj Once a manВҰ57224 plantedВҰ57226 a vineyardВҰ57227 andВҰ57213 rentedВҰ57230 itВҰ57231 out to tenantВҰ57232 farmersВҰ57232 before heading off on his trips.\wj*
\v 10 \wj At the appropriate time of the year, he sent a slave to the tenants to collect his percentage of the profits, butВҰ57260 they beat up the slave andВҰ57239 sent him back empty-handed.\wj*
\v 11 \wj SoВҰ57268 he sent anotherВҰ57273 slaveВҰ57276, but they also beat that one andВҰ57268 dishonouredВҰ57282 him, thenВҰ57268 sent him back empty-handed.\wj*
\v 12 \wj SoВҰ57286 the man sent a thirdВҰ57289 slave, and theyВҰ57292 also woundedВҰ57297 this one and threw him \add вүҲoff the property\add*.\wj*
\v 13 \wj SoВҰ57304 the masterВҰ57306 of the vineyardВҰ57308 asked \+add himself\+add*, вҖҳWhat will I do now? \+add Ah,\+add* I'll send myВҰ57315 dear sonвҖ”perhapsВҰ57319 they'll be swayedВҰ57322 by him.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 14 \wj But when the tenantsВҰ57327 saw the son, they reasonedВҰ57328 among themselves, вҖҳThis is the heir. If we killВҰ57339 him, then \+add his\+add* inheritanceВҰ57347 will becomeВҰ57345 ours.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 15 \wj So they threw him \add вүҲoff the property\add* andВҰ57348 killedВҰ57357 him.\wj*
\p \wj So thenВҰ57348, what will the masterВҰ57363 of the vineyard do to them?\wj*
\v 16 \wj He'll go \+add to the vineyard\+add* and destroyВҰ57368 those tenantВҰ57370 farmersВҰ57370, and will \+add lease\+add* the vineyard out to othersВҰ57377.\wj*вҖқ
\p The people listening looked at Yeshua and saidВҰ57382, вҖңSurely that could never happen.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 \x + \xo 20:17: \xt Psa 118:22.\x*But he looked them \add in the eyes\add* and asked, вҖң\wj Then what is this statement that was writtenВҰ57394 \+add in the scriptures\+add*?\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳThe stone whichВҰ57397 the buildersВҰ57400 rejectedВҰ57398,\wj*
\q1 \wj that one became the \+add most important\+add* stone.вҖҷ\wj*
\m
\v 18 \wj EveryoneВҰ57406 who falls onto that stone will be shatteredВҰ57413, and whoever that stone falls on will be pulverisedВҰ57420.\wj*вҖқ
