\r (Mark 14:10-11; Mat. 26:14-16)
\p
\v 3 ThenВҰ58709 SatanВҰ58711 entered YudasВҰ58714 IscariotВҰ58718, one of the twelveВҰ58725 \add apprentices\add*.
\v 4 He left \add the others\add* and went to the chiefВҰ58730 priestsВҰ58730 and \add their\add* officersВҰ58736 to discuss a way that he could turn Yeshua over to them.
\v 5 They were very pleased andВҰ58748 decidedВҰ58749 to giveВҰ58753 himВҰ58750 some silverВҰ58751,
\v 6 so agreeing to thatВҰ58760, he \add started\add* lookingВҰ58758 forВҰ58758 an opportunityВҰ58759 to turn Yeshua over to them \add sometime when he wasn't surrounded by\add* a crowdВҰ58765.
\s1 Yeshua organises their Passover dinner
\rem /s1 The Last Supper; The Preparation of the Passover; Jesus Prepares to Eat the Passover Meal
\r (Yhn 13:21-30; Mark 14:12-21; Mat. 26:17-25)
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ58768 the dayВҰ58770 of the flat breadВҰ58773 dinner arrived when the Passover celebration is observed.
\v 8 Yeshua sentВҰ58782 PeterВҰ58784 and Yohan, telling them, вҖң\wj Go on ahead and prepareВҰ58789 our Passover meal ready for us to eatВҰ58794.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңWhereВҰ58799 should weВҰ58801 prepareВҰ58801 it?вҖқ theyВҰ58795 asked.
\v 10 вҖң\wj ListenВҰ58811,\wj*вҖқ he saidВҰ58809, вҖң\wj go ahead andВҰ58808 when you enterВҰ58836 the cityВҰ58817 you'll meet a manВҰ58822 carrying a pitcherВҰ58824 of waterВҰ58825. Follow him into the houseВҰ58831 thatВҰ58833 he goes into.\wj*
\v 11 \wj ThenВҰ58837 tell the home-owner that the teacherВҰ58847 wants to know whereВҰ58853 the guestВҰ58851 roomВҰ58851 is so that he can eatВҰ58860 the Passover meal with his followers\wj*
\v 12 \wj andВҰ58862 he'll show you a largeВҰ58867 upperВҰ58865 roomВҰ58865 that's already set up. \+add That's where\+add* you should prepareВҰ58871 \+add the meal\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\v 13 SoВҰ58873 \add the two of them\add* went on \add ahead\add* and foundВҰ58874 itВҰ58874 \add exactly\add* like he'd told them, and so they preparedВҰ58881 the Passover \add dinner\add*.
\s1 The cups and the bread at dinner
\rem /s1 The Institution of the Lord's Supper
\r (Mark 14:22-26; Mat. 26:26-30; 1 Cor. 11:23-25)
\p
\v 14 When it was time to eat, Yeshua andВҰ58890 his apprentices satВҰ58889 down \add together\add*
\v 15 andВҰ58896 he told them, вҖң\wj I've been really looking forward to eating this pass-overВҰ58904 dinner with you all beforeВҰ58908 my timeВҰ58909 of sufferingВҰ58911 begins,\wj*
\v 16 \wj becauseВҰ58913 I'm telling you thatВҰ58926 I certainly won'tВҰ58918 eatВҰ58919 it \+add again\+add* untilВҰ58925 it's fulfilledВҰ58929 in God's kingdomВҰ58932.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ58935 when the \add wine\add* cup was passed to him, he gaveВҰ58939 thanksВҰ58939 and saidВҰ58940, вҖң\wj Take this and share it amongВҰ58945 yourselves,\wj*
\v 18 \wj becauseВҰ58950 I'm telling youВҰ58951 thatВҰ58969 after this, I won'tВҰ58957 drinkВҰ58958 the product of the vines \+add again\+add* untilВҰ58967 God's kingdomВҰ58973 comes.\wj*
\p
\v 19 ThenВҰ58977 picking up \add some\add* bread and giving thanksВҰ58980, he brokeВҰ58981 the bread \add apart\add* and gaveВҰ58980 it to them sayingВҰ58986, вҖң\wj This is myВҰ58992 bodyВҰ58991 whichВҰ58993 is beingВҰ58996 given for you all. Do this when you rememberВҰ59004 me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 20 \x + \xo 22:20: \xt Jer 31:31-34.\x*Similarly with the cup \add of wine\add* thatВҰ59011 comes afterВҰ59010 they've eaten, he said, вҖң\wj This cup is the new agreement in myВҰ59024 bloodВҰ59023 which will be pouredВҰ59029 out for you all.\wj*
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 22:21: \xt Psa 41:9.\x*вҖң\wj HoweverВҰ59030, the one who will turn me in is sitting with me at the tableВҰ59041.\wj*
\v 22 \wj Now, humanity's child has to endure what's been \+add previously\+add* designatedВҰ59054, but on the otherВҰ59056 hand, it won't end well for the man who turns him in.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The apprentices argue about being the greatest
\p
\v 23 This \add got them\add* debatingВҰ59069 among themselvesВҰ59072 about whichВҰ59073 one of them itВҰ59076 mightВҰ59076 be who was goingВҰ59082 to do thatВҰ59073
\rem /s1 The Dispute about Greatness; The Argument about Greatness
\v 24 \x + \xo 22:24: \xt Mrk 9:34; Mat 18:1; Luk 9:46.\x*andВҰ59086 itВҰ59085 soon turned into a dispute between them about whichВҰ59095 one of them was the greatestВҰ59100,
\v 25 so Yeshua saidВҰ59103, вҖң\wj In other countries, the kingsВҰ59106 are the mastersВҰ59109 over the people andВҰ59111 they call themselves вҖҳbenefactorsВҰ59120вҖҷ of those they have authorityВҰ59116 over.\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 22:26: \xt Mrk 9:35; Mat 23:11.\x*\wj But all of you shouldn'tВҰ59124 be like that, butВҰ59123 rather the greatestВҰ59128 one of you should become like the youngestВҰ59135, and the one who leads you all should become like the servant.\wj*
\v 27 \x + \xo 22:27: \xt Yhn 13:12-15.\x*\wj BecauseВҰ59146 who is greaterВҰ59148: the one on the couch, or the one who's serving? Isn't it the one on the couch? But among all of you, I'm like the one serving\wj*
\v 28 \wj andВҰ59178 youВҰ59177 all are the ones who have stuck with me even in myВҰ59195 trialsВҰ59194.\wj*
\p
\v 29 вҖң\wj And I'm making an agreement with youВҰ59199 (just like myВҰ59206 fatherВҰ59205 agreed that the kingdomВҰ59207 would be mine),\wj*
\v 30 \x + \xo 22:30: \xt Mat 19:28.\x*\wj so that you all will be able to eat and drinkВҰ59211 at my tableВҰ59214 in my kingdomВҰ59218, and you'll sit on thronesВҰ59228 judgingВҰ59234 the twelveВҰ59232 tribesВҰ59233 of YisraelВҰ59236.\wj*
\s1 Yeshua predicts Peter's denial
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts Peter's Denial
\r (Yhn 13:36-38; Mark 14:27-31; Mat. 26:31-35)
\p
\v 31 вҖң\wj Simon, Simon, SatanВҰ59245 has requestedВҰ59247 to sift youВҰ59248 all like wheatВҰ59253 \+add grains\+add*,\wj*
\v 32 \wj but I interceded for you that your faithВҰ59264 wouldn't fail and that once you turn back again, you'll strengthenВҰ59273 your brothersВҰ59275.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 33 вҖң\nd MasterВҰ59282\nd*,вҖқ Simon respondedВҰ59280, вҖңI'm prepared to go to prisonВҰ59289 with youВҰ59284, or even to die.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj I can tell you, PeterВҰ59299,\wj*вҖқ replied Yeshua, вҖң\wj that the roosterВҰ59305 certainly won't crow todayВҰ59304 untilВҰ59306 you've gone andВҰ59295 threeВҰ59310 times denied even knowingВҰ59314 me.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Take a wallet, backpack, and sword now
\rem /s1 Purse, Bag, and Sword
\p
\v 35 \x + \xo 22:35: \xt Mrk 6:8-9; Mat 10:9-10; Luk 9:3; 10:4.\x*ThenВҰ59316 Yeshua told them, вҖң\wj When I sentВҰ59320 you all out without a walletВҰ59323 or backpack or spare sandalsВҰ59327, did you have to go without anythingВҰ59329?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңNothing,вҖқ they answered.
\p
\v 36 вҖң\wj But now,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua continuedВҰ59338, вҖң\wj if you have a walletВҰ59347, takeВҰ59348 itВҰ59348 and same with a backpack. If you don'tВҰ59355 have a swordВҰ59366, sell your coatВҰ59361 and buy one,\wj*
\v 37 \x + \xo 22:37: \xt Isa 53:12.\x*\wj becauseВҰ59390 it was written that вҖҳhe was considered to be a lawbreakerвҖҷ and I'm telling you all that everything that was written about me, will be fulfilledВҰ59377 and \+add my time here\+add* is soon about to endВҰ59396.\wj*
\p
\v 38 вҖң\nd MasterВҰ59402\nd*,вҖқ they said, вҖңwe've got two swordsВҰ59406 here.вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj That's plenty,\wj*вҖқ he replied.
\s1 Yeshua prays in the garden
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays on the Mount of Olives
\r (Mark 14:32-42; Mat. 26:36-46)
\p
\v 39 ThenВҰ59416 leaving the \add upper room\add*, he went to the MountВҰ59426 of OlivesВҰ59428 as usual andВҰ59416 his apprenticesВҰ59434 followedВҰ59429 him.
\v 40 When they got to the placeВҰ59440, he told them, вҖң\wj \+add You all\+add* pray that you won'tВҰ59445 \+add give\+add* in to temptationВҰ59449.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 41 ThenВҰ59450 he went on several metres, andВҰ59450 kneeling \add on the ground\add*, he prayedВҰ59464,
\v 42 вҖң\wj Father, if you want, \+add allow me to avoid this suffering\+add*, howeverВҰ59478, I want to do what you wantвҖ”not \+add just\+add* what I want.\wj*вҖқ
\v 43 в—ҳ
\v 44 в—ҳ
\p
\v 45 ThenВҰ59526 standing again after praying, he went \add back\add* to the apprenticesВҰ59536 andВҰ59526 foundВҰ59538 that they'd fallenВҰ59541 asleepВҰ59541 from the sorrowВҰ59545
\v 46 and heВҰ59547 asked them, вҖң\wj Why are you all sleepingВҰ59550? Sit up and pray that you won'tВҰ59554 \+add give\+add* in to temptationВҰ59557.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is arrested at night
\rem /s1 Jesus Arrested; The Arrest of Jesus; The Betrayal and Arrest of Jesus; Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested; The trial and crucifixion of Jesus
\r (Yhn 18:3-11; Mark 14:43-50; Mat. 26:47-56)
\p
\v 47 While he was still speakingВҰ59562, wowВҰ59563, a crowdВҰ59564 \add turned up\add* with YudasВҰ59571 \add Iscariot\add* in the front, and he went up to \nd Yeshua\nd* to kissВҰ59597 him.
\v 48 But \nd Yeshua\nd* asked himВҰ59608, вҖң\wj YudasВҰ59609, are youВҰ59616 turning in humanity's child with a kissВҰ59611?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 49 When the other apprentices aroundВҰ59620 Yeshua saw what was about to happen, theyВҰ59625 asked, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ59629\nd*, should weВҰ59632 attack with our swordsВҰ59634?вҖқ
\v 50 ThenВҰ59635 one of them slashed at the chiefВҰ59644 priest'sВҰ59644 slaveВҰ59642 andВҰ59647 sliced off hisВҰ59654 rightВҰ59656 earВҰ59653.
\p
\v 51 вҖң\wj That's gone far enough!\wj*вҖқ countered \nd Yeshua\nd*, andВҰ59666 touchingВҰ59667 \add the side of \add* the man's head, he healedВҰ59676 him.
\p
\v 52 ThenВҰ59683 \nd Yeshua\nd* spoke to those who had comeВҰ59688 to capture himВҰ59691вҖ”the chiefВҰ59693 priestsВҰ59693 and templeВҰ59698 officersВҰ59695 and the local eldersВҰ59700, вҖң\wj SoВҰ59683 youВҰ59705 all cameВҰ59705 out here with swordsВҰ59707 and clubsВҰ59709 as if I was a robberВҰ59703?\wj*
\v 53 \x + \xo 22:53: \xt Luk 19:47; 21:37.\x*\wj I was there in the templeВҰ59719 with you all everydayВҰ59711 and yet you didn'tВҰ59722 arrest me \+add there\+add*. Yes, because this is yourВҰ59733 time: with the powerВҰ59738 of the darknessВҰ59741.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Peter denies knowing Yeshua
\rem /s1 Peter Disowns Jesus; Peter Denies Jesus
\r (Yhn 18:12-18,25-27; Mark 14:53-54,66-72; Mat. 26:57-58,69-75)
\p
\v 54 ThenВҰ59744 after capturingВҰ59743 Yeshua, they led him along to the chiefВҰ59757 priest'sВҰ59757 houseВҰ59754, butВҰ59759 PeterВҰ59760 followedВҰ59761 them from a distance.
\v 55 \add The staff at the chief priest's place\add* had lit a fireВҰ59768 to sit around in the middle of the courtyardВҰ59774, andВҰ59776 PeterВҰ59783 \add slipped in\add* with them.
\v 56 ThenВҰ59792 a servantВҰ59794 girlВҰ59794 noticed him in the lightВҰ59799, andВҰ59792 peering at him she saidВҰ59803, вҖңThis man was with him as well.вҖқ
\p
\v 57 But Peter disownedВҰ59811 him, sayingВҰ59813, вҖңWoman, I don'tВҰ59815 \add even\add* know him.вҖқ
\p
\v 58 A littleВҰ59821 while later, someone else noticed himВҰ59825 andВҰ59819 said, вҖңYou're also one of them!вҖқ
\p вҖңMan, I'm not!вҖқ PeterВҰ59837 retorted.
\p
\v 59 About an hourВҰ59848 later, someone else insistedВҰ59852 on sayingВҰ59853, вҖңThis fellow was definitely with himВҰ59861 becauseВҰ59864 he's also a GalileanВҰ59865!вҖқ
\p
\v 60 вҖңMan, I don'tВҰ59872 know what you'reВҰ59876 talkingВҰ59881 about!вҖқ PeterВҰ59870 respondedВҰ59867, andВҰ59877 while he was stillВҰ59879 speakingВҰ59881, the roosterВҰ59886 crowedВҰ59884.
\p
\v 61 JustВҰ59903 thenВҰ59887 the master turnedВҰ59888 and looked at PeterВҰ59898, and he \add suddenly\add* remembered what the master had said, вҖң\wj BeforeВҰ59914 the roosterВҰ59916 crows todayВҰ59918, threeВҰ59922 times you'll deny \+add even\+add* knowing me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 62 ThenВҰ59926 Peter went out \add of the courtyard\add* andВҰ59926 cried \add like a baby\add*.
\s1 Yeshua is mocked and beaten
\rem /s1 The Guards Mock Jesus; Jesus Is Mocked and Beaten; The Mocking and Beating of Jesus
\r (Mark 14:65; Mat. 26:67-68)
\p
\v 63 \add Meanwhile\add* the \add officers\add* who were holdingВҰ59938 Yeshua started mockingВҰ59942 him andВҰ59933 beatingВҰ59944 him.
\v 64 They blindfoldedВҰ59946 him and thenВҰ59945 challenged him, вҖңProphesyВҰ59959 and tell us who just slapped you!вҖқ
\v 65 as well as sayingВҰ59971 many otherВҰ59968 things to insult himВҰ59974.
\s1 Yeshua's brief interrogation by the Jewish council
\rem /s1 Jesus before the Council; Jesus Before Pilate and Herod
\r (Yhn 18:19-24; Mark 14:55-64; Mat. 26:59-66)
\p
\v 66 As the daylight came, the council of local eldersВҰ59982 including both the chiefВҰ59986 priestsВҰ59986 and the religiousВҰ59989 teachersВҰ59989, gatheredВҰ59980 togetherВҰ59980 and Yeshua was led in to the council
\v 67 who demanded, вҖңIf you'reВҰ60001 the \nd messiahВҰ60004\nd*, tell us so.вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj Even if I told you,\wj*вҖқ he replied, вҖң\wj you certainly wouldn't believeВҰ60017 me,\wj*
\v 68 \wj and if I asked you all anything, you certainly wouldn't answerВҰ60024.\wj*
\v 69 \wj ButВҰ60031 from now on, humanity's child will be sittingВҰ60037 in the seat of powerВҰ60041 at God's rightВҰ60039 \+add hand\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 70 вҖңSoВҰ60056 thenВҰ60056, you \em are\em* God's son!вҖқ they all reacted.
\p вҖң\wj \+add Well,\+add* you're all saying that I am,\wj*вҖқ he saidВҰ60044.
\p
\v 71 вҖңWhy would we need any more witnesses than this?вҖқ they asked, вҖңbecauseВҰ60079 we heardВҰ60080 itВҰ60080 \add ourselvesВҰ60077\add* straight out of hisВҰ60084 mouthВҰ60083.вҖқ
\c 23
\s1 Yeshua is taken to Pilate
\rem /s1 Jesus before Pilate; Jesus' Trial before Pilate
\r (Yhn 18:28-38; Mark 15:1-5; Mat. 27:1-2,11-14)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ60085 the whole group of \add @Jewish leaders\add* stood up andВҰ60085 led himВҰ60094 to PilateВҰ60098
\v 2 where theyВҰ60099 started to bring their accusationsВҰ60101, вҖңWe foundВҰ60106 this manВҰ60105 pervertingВҰ60108 ourВҰ60111 nationВҰ60110 and telling the people not to pay taxesВҰ60115 to CaesarВҰ60117. He calls himselfВҰ60123 the \nd messiahВҰ60125\nd* and claims to be a kingВҰ60126.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңAre you the kingВҰ60138 of the Jews?вҖқ PilateВҰ60130 askedВҰ60131 him.
\p вҖң\wj You're the one saying it,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answeredВҰ60143.
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ60153 PilateВҰ60154 told the chiefВҰ60158 priestsВҰ60158 andВҰ60159 the crowdsВҰ60161, вҖңI can'tВҰ60162 find anything that this manВҰ60167 is guiltyВҰ60164 of.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 But theyВҰ60169 \add kept\add* insistingВҰ60172, вҖңHe's been stirringВҰ60175 up the peopleВҰ60178, teachingВҰ60179 throughoutВҰ60180 all YudeaВҰ60184. He started in GalileeВҰ60189 then worked his way all the way down here.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is taken to Herod
\rem /s1 Jesus before Herod
\p
\v 6 When PilateВҰ60192 heardВҰ60195 that, he askedВҰ60200 if the prisoner was a GalileanВҰ60207,
\v 7 andВҰ60209 when he discovered that he was from \add King\add* Herod's jurisdiction, he sentВҰ60218 him across to Herod as he also happened to be in Yerushalem at that time.
\v 8 HerodВҰ60241 was very pleased when he saw Yeshua \add being brought in\add* because he'd been wantingВҰ60257 to see him for quite some time because of everything he'd heard about him. He was hopingВҰ60267 to see Yeshua do a miracle \add in front of his eyes\add*
\v 9 andВҰ60278 asked him lots of questions, but Yeshua didn't answerВҰ60287 any of them.
\v 10 Meanwhile the chiefВҰ60295 priestsВҰ60295 andВҰ60296 the religiousВҰ60298 teachersВҰ60298 were standing there loudly making many accusationsВҰ60300 againstВҰ60301 himВҰ60301.
\v 11 ThenВҰ60304 Herod and hisВҰ60312 soldiers also insulted and mockedВҰ60314 Yeshua, and dressing him in posh clothesВҰ60318, \add @Herod\add* sentВҰ60321 him back to PilateВҰ60324.
\v 12 After that dayВҰ60346, HerodВҰ60334 andВҰ60336 PilateВҰ60338 becameВҰ60326 friendsВҰ60331 with each other. (Before thenВҰ60328 they'd opposed each other.)
\s1 The innocent prisoner sentenced to death
\rem /s1 Jesus Sentenced to Death; Jesus Is Sentenced to Death
\r (Yhn 18:39вҖ“19:16; Mark 15:6-15; Mat. 27:15-26)
\p
\v 13 SoВҰ60361 PilateВҰ60360 calledВҰ60363 togetherВҰ60363 the chiefВҰ60366 priestsВҰ60366 and the local leaders and the peopleВҰ60373
\v 14 and told them, вҖңYou broughtВҰ60378 this man to me for stirring up the peopleВҰ60386, but listen, I've examinedВҰ60395 him in front of you all and I find him to be not guiltyВҰ60402 of anything thatВҰ60405 you're all accusingВҰ60406 him of,
\v 15 andВҰ60421 HerodВҰ60412 didn'tВҰ60411 either, becauseВҰ60415 he \add just\add* sentВҰ60413 him back to us. Now listen, he's done nothingВҰ60424 worthyВҰ60425 of a deathВҰ60426 sentence
\v 16 so I'll have him disciplinedВҰ60432 and then discharged.
\p
\v 17 в—ҳ
\v 18 But they all yelledВҰ60447 out in unison, вҖңTake him away andВҰ60459 release BarabbasВҰ60462 instead!вҖқ
\v 19 (Barabbas had been thrownВҰ60475 into prisonВҰ60480 for murderВҰ60473 after an uprising that had occurred in the cityВҰ60471.)
\p
\v 20 PilateВҰ60486 calledВҰ60487 out againВҰ60482 to them wantingВҰ60490 to release \nd Yeshua\nd*
\v 21 butВҰ60495 they kept yelling, вҖңExecute him on a post! Execute him on a post!вҖқ
\p
\v 22 He tried a thirdВҰ60508 time, вҖңButВҰ60507 what crime has this manВҰ60516 committed? I've foundВҰ60522 nothing worthy of the deathВҰ60521 sentence, so I'll disciplineВҰ60526 him andВҰ60507 thenВҰ60507 release him.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ButВҰ60532 theyВҰ60531 kept loudlyВҰ60536 insisting that he be executedВҰ60539 on a post, andВҰ60542 the yelling \add of the crowd was strong enough\add* to convince Pilate,
\v 24 so he conceded to theirВҰ60561 requestВҰ60560
\v 25 and released the one thrownВҰ60572 into prisonВҰ60577 for murderВҰ60570 and rebellion, but he conceded \add to sentence\add* \nd YeshuaВҰ60584\nd* as they had wanted.
\s1 Yeshua is hung on a pole
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Crucified; The Crucifixion of Jesus
\r (Yhn 19:17-27; Mark 15:21-32; Mat. 27:32-44)
\p
\v 26 As \add the Roman soldiers\add* led Yeshua \add out of the city\add*, they grabbed a man that was comingВҰ60606 in from the countrysideВҰ60608. He was SimonВҰ60597 from CyreneВҰ60603, and they \add forced\add* him to carryВҰ60615 the post and follow along behindВҰ60616 Yeshua.
\p
\v 27 Following along behind them, was a large crowdВҰ60624 of peopleВҰ60627 including womenВҰ60629 who were wailing for Yeshua andВҰ60620 \add вүҲchanting sad songs\add*,
\v 28 butВҰ60639 he turnedВҰ60638 to them and spoke, вҖң\wj Women of Yerushalem, don'tВҰ60651 weep for me. Weep for yourselvesВҰ60660 and for yourВҰ60666 childrenВҰ60665,\wj*
\v 29 \wj because the time is comingВҰ60669 when they'll say, вҖҳBlessedВҰ60677 are the childless couples and the women who never bore or raised a child.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 30 \x + \xo 23:30: \xt Hos 10:8; Rev 6:16.\x*\wj Then they'll start begging the mountainsВҰ60699 to fall on top of them andВҰ60703 begging the hillsВҰ60705 to smother them,\wj*
\v 31 \wj because if this is what happens \+add while we're still a nation\+add*, what will happen \+add when the country is gone\+add*?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 32 There were also twoВҰ60729 otherВҰ60726 criminalsВҰ60728 beingВҰ60723 led along to be executed with Yeshua.
\p
\v 33 When they got to the placeВҰ60739 named вҖҳThe SkullвҖҷ, they attached Yeshua onto a post\f + \fr 23:33 \ft Luke doesn't state whether or not the post had a cross-piece (which would then form a cross or a T).\f* andВҰ60733 the same for the \add two\add* criminalsВҰ60750, one on each side of himВҰ60747,
\v 34 \x + \xo 23:34: \xt Psa 22:18.\x*butВҰ60777 when theyВҰ60781 divided hisВҰ60780 clothesВҰ60779, \add the soldiers\add* threw dice \add to divide them up\add*.
\p
\v 35 \x + \xo 23:35: \xt Psa 22:7-8.\x*The peopleВҰ60790 observingВҰ60791 were standing there, and some of the \add Jewish\add* leaders were there too, sneeringВҰ60794 at him and sayingВҰ60802, вҖңHe savedВҰ60807 othersВҰ60805, so now if he's God's son, the chosen \nd messiahВҰ60819\nd*, let him saveВҰ60808 himselfВҰ60809.вҖқ
\p
\v 36 The soldiersВҰ60836 also mockedВҰ60831 him, going up andВҰ60832 offeringВҰ60842 cheap wine to him,
\v 37 sayingВҰ60846, вҖңIf you'reВҰ60849 the kingВҰ60852 of the Jews, then saveВҰ60860 yourselfВҰ60861,вҖқ
